title: salmon patties
directions: Beat eggs; add salmon and other ingredients.
Make into patties and fry in pan.

title: c.m.p. cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: dill bread
directions: In small bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water. In large bowl, combine cottage cheese, sugar, butter, dill weed, chives, salt, soda and egg; beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat in yeast mixture. Add 1 1/2 cups of flour. Gradually mix in enough of remaining flour by hand to form stiff, smooth dough. Cover bowl with a damp towel. Let dough rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour. Punch dough down (dough will be moist and sticky). Turn dough into buttered souffle dish. Let rise until doubled, 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Yields 1 loaf.

title: crumb cake
directions: *soured cream or plain cream soured with 1 Tbsp. vinegar to 1 c. cream

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese together.
Spread in baked pie shells.
Cover cream cheese with sliced peaches, filling to the top of pie shells.
Boil cornstarch, water and 1 cup sugar until thickened, then add Jell-O and set aside to cool.
Pour Jell-O (cooled) over peaches.
Congeal in refrigerator for several hours.
Cover with whipped topping before serving.
This makes 2 pies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and add all other ingredients except stuffing.
Mix melted margarine with stuffing mix.
Place layer of this in bottom of greased casserole dish and add squash mixture.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix together the sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook on High 20 to 22 minutes.
While syrup cooks, beat egg whites until stiff peak forms in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually pour hot mixture in a thin stream over egg whites while beating at high speed until mixture thickens and candy starts to lose its gloss.
Beating may require about 15 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon until crispy.
Set aside.
Cook hamburger, green pepper, mushrooms and onion until done.
Add stewed tomatoes; simmer.
Cook rice; break up bacon and add to hamburger mixture. When rice is done, use your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Mix all together.
Add cheese if you want.
Smaller portions use less time to make.
This takes 1 1/2 hours.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Put asparagus on bottom of an 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Beat together milk and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and pour over the asparagus.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center of quiche comes out clean.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix water, sugar and lemonade Kool-Aid.
Squeeze lemons.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Combine ice cream, Cool Whip, peanut butter and half of chopped peanuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into pie shell.
Top with rest of peanuts.
Sprinkle chocolate syrup over the top of the pie and freeze.

title: prune cake delight
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Blend well. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Blend well. Add buttermilk and vanilla. Blend well. Fold in prunes and chopped pecans. Bake in greased, floured 9 x 13 pan at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° in casserole dish for 25 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch strips.
Saute quickly in 1 tablespoon oil until brown.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Add 2 tablespoons oil to the pan and saute mushrooms and onions about 5 to 8 minutes.
Add steak, bouillon and wine; simmer about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add basil, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes. Slowly add warm sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: tortellini and crab salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and toss with salad dressing.

title: chilies rellenos
directions: Cut chilies down the middle, open up and fill each with cheese (and beef and onions, if desired).
Dust with flour and set aside. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in 1 teaspoon flour and salt to taste.
Add egg yolks.
Heat oil in a skillet.
Dip chilies one at a time in egg mixture and place in skillet.
Turn and cook until golden brown on both sides.
Serve immediately.

title: rolled chicken
directions: Filling:
Cook mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes; blend in flour, stir in cream, salt and pepper.
Cook until thick; stir in cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Cool at least one hour or more.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put in boiler the chocolate, butter, flour, salt and scalded milk.
Stir, while cooking, about 15 minutes.
Add egg yolks and cook 2 minutes longer.
Add vanilla and remove from heat.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: chocolate chip coconut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl; set aside.
Combine butter, sugars and vanilla extract in large bowl; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; blend well.
Stir in Nestle semi-sweet real chocolate morsels and coconut.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch well-greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: christmas german oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Cream the margarine and sugar.
Mix with oats.
Add the eggs and vanilla. Add flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maraschino cherry nut cake
directions: Cream the shortening; add sugar gradually and cream together thoroughly.
Sift flour once before measuring.
Mix nuts and cherries and dredge with 2 tablespoons of flour.
Mix and sift remainder of flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with liquid.
Blend in nuts and cherries. Fold in egg whites which have been beaten until stiff, but not dry.
Pour into well-greased and floured cake pan and bake 50 minutes at 350° in 8-inch pan.
Cool and frost with white icing.

title: mock swiss steak
directions: Pat into 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Chill overnight.
Cut in six pieces.
Dredge in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in small amount of oil.
Put in roaster.
Add 1 cup water.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: the perfect meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Form into loaf; put into 11 x 14-inch pan.
Cover loaf with 1 can tomato sauce.
Put 1/2 cup water in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jalapeno cocktail pie
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 3-quart baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
(May prepare, refrigerate overnight and bake the next day.)

title: sweet and sour chicken kabobs
directions: Place chicken cubes and green pepper pieces in shallow dish. Drain pineapple reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Combine pineapple juice, brown sugar, soy sauce, vinegar, garlic powder and ginger.
Pour over chicken and green pepper slices.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours. Thread chicken, pineapple and green peppers onto 6 long skewers. Cook over grill.

title: chicken-broccoli skillet(low calorie)
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Cook chicken and onion quickly in hot margarine.
Stir in broccoli, lemon juice, thyme, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Cook, uncovered, 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cook, covered, 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: lemon cheese fill-ups
directions: Combine butter, cream cheese, confectioners sugar, flour, 1 teaspoon lemon juice and 1 teaspoon peel.
Mix at low speed until dough forms.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and margarine and put 2/3 of it in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with only 2 cups milk in a large bowl. Add ice cream.
Pour this mixture over crumbs and refrigerate. When set, put Cool Whip over the top.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Decorate with maraschino cherries if you wish.

title: zesty vidalia onion dip
directions: Blend sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover. Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and milk in saucepan.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet or waxed paper.

title: chocolate-malt cheese cake
directions: Mix well and pat into pan.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg until fluffy.
Add to dry ingredients with zucchini, blending well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare jello as directed, but substitute pineapple juice for water.
Jell.
Whip 1 package of Dream Whip and chill.
Beat jelled jello and add crushed pineapple and Dream Whip.
Crumble angel food cake in bottom of cake pan and pour mixture over it. Mix lightly and smooth into pan.
Top with remaining Dream Whip and chill.
Refrigerate.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large skillet. Cook over medium heat until the mixture simmers. Add carrots and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread evenly in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Check bottom occasionally.
Stir so as not to burn.
May sprinkle corn flakes and butter on top before baking.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Pour all ingredients into large bowl and beat for 2 minutes (medium speed).
Pour into 9 x 11 x 12-inch pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bob davis' favorite breakfast casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and mushrooms in small amount of butter; brown sausage and drain.
Put bread in bottom of long bread pan; mix milk and eggs well.
Add sausage, vegetables and
cheese. Pour over bread.
Let set in fridge overnight.
Pour soup over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift together and add to ingredients, flour, baking powder, cloves, soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Bake for 1 hour and 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peach jello pie
directions: Sprinkle peaches with 1/2 cup sugar. Set aside. Combine powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese. Spread on bottom of each crust. On medium heat, cook 1 cup sugar, jello, water and cornstarch until thick. Let cool. Add drained peaches. Spread on top of pie.

title: do-it-yourself ice cream sandwiches
directions: Spread softened ice cream to the edge of any appropriate cookie (graham crackers are good, but most any will do, even Oreos).
Press on top cookie gently.
Wrap or stack in foil or plastic wrap and freeze.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat together egg yolks, butter and lemon.
Then add sugar, milk and flour.
Flour
into 3 stiffly beaten egg whites and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Brown beef in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat. Combine cheeses and sour cream.
Add onion, parsley and pepper to taste.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Break eggs into large bowl and whip until frothy.
Add potatoes, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend well. Add milk and stir in well.
Spoon filling into pastry shell.

title: florida sherbet
directions: Cook milk and sugar to just under the boiling point.
Cool and place in ice cube tray; freeze to mushy stage.
Remove; add juice of oranges and lemon.
Beat with beater and return to tray to freeze, stirring occasionally during freezing.
(I sometimes substitute a small can of crushed pineapple for oranges and lemon.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Use Velveeta and Cheddar cheese to make 1 1/2 cups when mixed together.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook at 350° in large casserole dish.

title: salad
directions: You can add 1 cup nuts (pecans or English walnuts).
Mix well. Chill and serve.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs with milk.
Add flour; mix well.
Add all other ingredients, including corn juice.
Mix well and drop in hot oil. Cook until golden brown all over.

title: hamburg cutlets
directions: Mix beef, parsley, salt and pepper (to taste), eggs and bread crumbs.
Make 6 to 8 patties and brown in oil.
Arrange in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Top with cheese.
Pour sauce over.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: church punch
directions: Make a syrup of water and sugar.
Mix with juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serves approximately 40.

title: pork and lima beans
directions: Soak the beans the night before and rinse in cold water.
Cook in 6 cups cold water and boil 2 minutes.
Remove and soak 1 hour.

title: meat casserole
directions: Fry chops until brown.
Place in casserole dish.
Over chop, place slices of onion, tomato and bell pepper.
Sprinkle with rice.
Mix soup and water; salt and pepper.
Pour over pork chops. Cover and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: baked sandwich
directions: Baking:
Mix beaten eggs, dry mustard, salt, pepper and milk. Pour over sandwiches and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 4 hours before baking.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal and date cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Simmer dates in juice until soft. Combine oats, flour, baking soda, spices and nuts.
Chop raisins in flour and add.
Put dates and liquid, melted butter and oil in a blender and puree until smooth.
Combine with dry ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: the best blueberry muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed. Place in muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time. Alternate milk and flour. Beat well. Add lemon extract. Pour into large tube pan that has been greased and floured. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Drain, wash (in cold water) and mash shrimp.
Combine with all other ingredients except cream cheese.
Spread softened cream cheese on a small plate and spread shrimp mixture on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: homemade meat pie
directions: Cook ground beef, add onions, salt and pepper.
Cook a few minutes, then add soup.
Mix together real well.
Pour mixture into pie shell, sprinkle cheese over top of mixture.
Place second pie shell on top.
Seal around edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut and serve.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; beat well.
Mix all ingredients, except crab and 1/4 cup sharp cheese.
Stir in crab meat; put remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 325°, uncovered.

title: old time fudge
directions: Grease pot with margarine (sides and bottom).
Mix sugar, salt, chocolate, syrup and milk until it comes to a full boil. Cook over medium heat until comes to a soft ball stage when dropped in a cup of cold water.
This normally only takes about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Mix well. Place pot in sink in cold water.
Beat until it loses its gloss and starts thickening up.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Bake in turkey or by itself.
Double if turkey over 12 pounds.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Insert metal blade in food processor.
Add all ingredients. Process until smooth.
Line a 2 cup mold with plastic wrap.
Leave extra to hang over edge.
Spoon in mixture.
Press to remove air spaces and to make a nice smooth shape when unmolded later.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Invert mold on serving plate.
Peel off plastic.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, cherry tomato halves and lemon slices.
Serve with crackers or toast squares.

title: aloha shrimp salad
directions: Bring water to a boil; add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Peel and devein, if desired.
Combine shrimp and remaining ingredients. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve on leaf lettuce or in pita bread.

title: venison stew
directions: Dissolve cubes in small amount of water.
Brown venison in butter.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until done.

title: brown rice pilaf
directions: Steam carrot and bell pepper, covered, 2 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain well; set aside.

title: broiled salmon steaks
directions: Combine butter and lemon juice and brush over fish.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 10 minutes.
Turn and brush over again and broil 5 minutes more.
Serve with sauce.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Sift the remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 18 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine ingredients in processor or blender until smooth; scrape sides often.
Makes 14 ounces.

title: chicken and sauerkraut
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Dry and sprinkle with salt and pepper; set aside.
Put sauerkraut in colander and soak, changing water several times.
Wring it out and let drain.
Brown chicken in oil, a few pieces at a time, and keep warm on a platter.
When chicken is done, add onions to fat and turn heat down.
Add garlic. When onions are clear, add sauerkraut and chicken stock.
Bring to a boil.
Add chilies.
Put in the chicken and let simmer about 1 hour.
(Gets better the longer it cooks.)

title: country captain chicken
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; shake to mix.
Add chicken pieces 1 or 2 at a time, to mixture in bag.
Shake to coat chicken with mixture.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef.
Add all remaining ingredients except parsley; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: strawberry-rhubarb puff
directions: Use a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: clay's jail house chili
directions: In Dutch oven over medium heat, brown meat until all pink color is gone.
Add onion, garlic, jalapenos, chili powder, cumin, oregano.
Cook about 20 minutes until vegies are very tender. Stir in tomatoes.
Add beef stock, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Add kidney beans.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add cayenne pepper to taste.
Serve hot with flour tortillas.

title: cinnamon ring
directions: Sprinkle chopped walnuts in greased 4 1/2-cup ring mold or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Separate biscuits; dip in butter, then in sugar mixture.
Place in pan overlapping slightly.
Tuck raisins in between biscuits.
Add any remaining sugar mixture and butter.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Invert pan to remove ring.
Serve warm.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Keep hot in crock-pot.

title: double tomato soup
directions: Peel and dice tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
Combine with soup and water in saucepan.
Add rice.
Cook until onion is done. Season.
I like to add 1 or 2 teaspoons of sugar.
Add water to your preferred consistency.
Will serve at least 3.

title: sugar-free glazed fruit
directions: Sprinkle Tang over sliced bananas.
Drain pineapple and fruit (reserve 1/3 cup juice).
Sprinkle dry pudding over all fruit. Mix lightly and refrigerate.

title: grilled corn
directions: Spray foil well with butter-flavor nonstick spray on one side only.
Place corn on cob (fresh) on sprayed side.
Wrap.
Cook on coals, turning once or twice.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: frittata(italian omelet)
directions: In 10 inch broiler- proof skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add broccoli, sweet pepper, onion, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper. Cook and stir till florets are crisp/tender, about 4 minutes for fresh broccoli and 5 minutes for frozen broccoli.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain and add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Mix noodles, meat and tomato juice. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add corn and pour into baking dish.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Put in bottom of 8 x 10-inch buttered baking dish.
Top with chopped onions.
Pour soup over hamburger and onions.
Cover tightly with frozen potato gems and bake in 350° oven until brown or cooked through.

title: german kuchen
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Add eggs. Mix in flour and salt. Add vanilla. Batter will be thick. Reserve about 1 cup of batter to use later for top.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches or two square pans, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
In medium bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup melted butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow to cool and frost.

title: deer stew
directions: Follow directions on beef stew package for meat.
Add vegetables as directed.
Meat does not need to be soaked.

title: michigan hot dog sauce
directions: Cook pepper and onion in butter until soft.
Add hamburg and brown.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add the egg and mix until beady (mix with knife and fork).
Sprinkle mixture over peaches.
Melt butter and pour over flour, etc.
Sprinkle well with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: zucchini relish
directions: In large enamel or stainless-steel pot, combine vegetables and salt; let stand 3 hours.
Rinse and drain, then set aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Separate egg yolks and whites.
Beat egg yolks and mix with 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Add to dry ingredients. Cook until thickened.
When thick, add vanilla and a tablespoon of butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: the christmas rainbow
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch layer pans at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan; poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Do not remove from pans.
Dissolve each package of gelatin separately in 1 cup boiling water.
Pour raspberry gelatin over 1 layer, lime over the other.
Chill 4 hours.
Unmold one layer onto serving plate.
Top with 1 cup of the whipped topping. Unmold second layer onto first.
Frost top and sides with remaining whipped topping.
Chill.
Garnish with flattened gumdrops to resemble holly.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Begin with darkest colored jello.
Mix 1 package jello in 1 cup hot water.
Take 1/2 cup of that mixture and add 1/3 cup sour cream in separate bowl.
Take remaining 1/2 cup and add 3 tablespoons cold water.
In lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pour sour cream mixture first.
Let mixture set in refrigerator for 20 minutes or until firm.
Add remaining (clear) jello for next layer.
Chill until firm.
Repeat using all 6 boxes of jello.

title: fish with tomato sauce
directions: In medium bowl, stir tomato sauce, parsley and oregano until well mixed. Set aside.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, butter or margarine, cook fillets, 2 or 3 minutes on each side until flaky.

title: easy almond cracker brittle
directions: Combine 3 ingredients and bring to a boil in saucepan.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Cover with Keebler Club crackers.
Pour liquid over crackers slowly until it soaks in.
Sprinkle almonds over all.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put half of stuffing in bottom of baking dish.
Put in melted butter and torn up chicken.
Mix 2 soups and pour over chicken. Put on the rest of the stuffing.
Pour broth over the whole layered dish.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: 2 minute microwave fudge
directions: Stir in all ingredients except margarine, until partially blended.
Put margarine on top and microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
Pour in wax paper-lined dish.
Chill 1 hour.

title: my squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender before measuring.
Drain water off. Add butter, salt, pepper and cream of mushroom.
Mix all and add beaten eggs, onion, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake (uncovered) at 375° for about 40 minutes. I add more cheese on top.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Break frozen banana in chunks.
In blender, combine banana, vanilla and milk; blend until smooth.
Sweeten with maple syrup, if desired.
Makes 1 (1 1/2 cup) serving.

title: strawberry cream cheese ice cream
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add strawberries and mix well.
Add egg/milk mixture to strawberry/cream cheese mixture and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding mix with milk.
Mix with sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Put this mixture between layers of vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: butternut casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir well.
Melt 1 tablespoon oleo in skillet.
Add apples and sugar.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes and drain.
Stir apples into squash.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over squash.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: inside out chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine pudding mix, cake mix, chocolate chips, milk and eggs in a very large bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended.
Fold in pecans.

title: venison dyson
directions: Cook venison in water until tender.
Add salt and pepper. Cool. Cut into small pieces and put in shallow pan.
Cover with the stock that it was cooked in. Put onion, flour, wine and bacon strips on top.
Bake for about 2 hours in a slow oven.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches and juice into square or round casserole dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches, spreading evenly to edges. Slice butter into pats and place evenly spaced over the cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: tuna spread
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Mix in other ingredients.
Spread on crackers to serve.
Tastes like smoked fish spread.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs and add milk and crumbs.
Add onions, corn, seasonings and melted butter.
Mix together well and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tomato-mozzarella salad
directions: Layer tomatoes and cheese in shallow dish.
In small jar with tight fitting lid, place oil, vinegar, parsley, onion, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and shake well.
Pour over tomatoes and cheese. Cover and refrigerate several hours, occasionally spooning dressing over tomato salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: glorious potatoes
directions: Mix all together and put in a large baking dish. Cover top with 2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: yummy taco dip
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Spread on a platter.
Cover with rest of ingredients.
Serve with taco chips and corn chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Tear beef into small pieces and mix into softened cream cheese.
Add garlic powder and mix well.
Shape into a ball or put into a bowl and refrigerate until firm and flavors are blended. Overnight is best, but a few hours will do.
Serve on crackers.

title: ladies' luncheon casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Place in a greased casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and macaroni bake
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add onions; cook until tender. Stir in tomato sauce, 1/2 c. parmesan cheese and spices; simmer 10 minutes. Prepare dinner at directed on package. Spread ground beef mixture onto bottom of 9 inch square baking dish. Top with dinner. Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat. Blend in flour. Gradually add milk; cook stirring constantly until thickened. Stir small amount of hot mixture into eggs; return to hot mixture. Pour over dinner; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar to make light syrup.
Mix bananas, juices and syrup.
Put into containers to freeze.
When ready to serve let thaw some, then add ginger ale.

title: apple sweet yams
directions: Peel and cube the yams.
Cook until tender.
Peel, core and cube the apples.
Layer the potatoes and the apples in a 2-quart baking dish, set aside.
Put the rest of the ingredients into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour the liquid over the potatoes and the apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 8 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together real well.
Fill cup about 1/3 to 1/2 full, then add hot water and stir well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all except broccoli
and let stand several hours or overnight, then pour over broccoli and mix well.

title: christmas holly
directions: Melt marshmallows and oleo together; add vanilla, green food coloring and corn flakes.
Mix together; drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Decorate with cinnamon red hots (3 or 4).
Store in tight container.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place on a rack in a shallow baking pan; set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, combine corn flake crumbs and parsley; set aside.
In another small bowl, combine yogurt, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Brush chicken with yogurt mixture, then sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 to 55 minutes, or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Makes 6 servings.

title: radford's brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk.
Beat well at medium speed.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir well with spoon.
Use 1 standard-sized tube pan or 3 foil loaf pans (7 7/8 x 3 7/8 x 2 1/2-inch).
Ice with favorite brown sugar icing. Bake tube cake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours; loaf cakes at 325° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix all except crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Crumble crackers on top and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pinwheel cookies
directions: Combine shortening, 1/3 cup butter, egg yolks and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix on low speed until blended. Set aside cocoa packet.
Gradually add cake mix.
Blend well.
Divide dough. Add cocoa packet and remaining 1 tablespoon butter to half of the dough.
Knead until well blended.
Roll out yellow dough between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Roll into rectangular shape. Repeat for chocolate dough.
Remove wax paper. Lay yellow dough on top of chocolate dough.
Roll up like jelly roll, rolling from wide side. Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: latin dip
directions: Chop onion into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend with mixer until thoroughly blended.
Store in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: frozen kahlua torte
directions: Spray a spring-form pan with Pam or very lightly wipe
pan with cooking oil.
In a bowl, mix together the Kahlua, milk and vanilla.
Mix 1/4 cup Kahlua mixture into Cool Whip.
Divide chocolate chip cookies into thirds.
Dip 1 cookie at a time, very quickly into the Kahlua mixture and layer bottom of pan. Divide Cool Whip into thirds and spread 1/3 over the first layer of cookies.
Layer a total of 3 layers of dipped cookies and Cool Whip, ending with Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast with water.
Add oleo and sugar, then egg and flour. Stir until well mixed.
Put in air-tight container and place in refrigerator.
Make sure container has some room for mixture to expand.

title: cande crab dip
directions: Hollow out one loaf of bread and cut up pieces of removed bread into bite size pieces.
Combine mayo, cheese, crab and onion in a baking dish and bake until hot and bubbly.
Pour into hollowed out bread and remaining bread that have been cut into bite size pieces.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
Add soups and mushrooms.
When thoroughly mixed, remove from heat and add sour cream and chicken.
Place back on stove to keep warm; stir often.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in milk and egg; mix again and add onion.
Mix again.
Batter will be thin.
Fry in deep fat or oil. Drop by spoon.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Place one layer of graham crackers in cake pan.
Pour approximately 1/2 inch of mixture.
Repeat process until mixture is gone.
It should make 2 to 3 layers.
Once done, place chocolate icing on top.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Toss carrots and raisins together.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over carrots and raisins.
Stir carefully and thoroughly.
Chill to blend flavors.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and season to taste.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Spread on open-faced buns.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until buns are lightly brown around edges and cheese is melted.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Peel, wash and slice potatoes (medium thick).
To bake faster, slice thinner.
Use baking dish, butter the bottom of dish.
Place sliced potatoes in
a layer.
Sprinkle with Italian dressing mix, then another layer of potatoes. Bake in a 325° oven until done.

title: german twists
directions: Mix and let rise in icebox or cold place for about 2 hours or overnight.

title: white salad
directions: Mix together.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.

title: english muffins
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine next 4 ingredients; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add yeast; mix.
Add enough of remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth (8 to 10 minutes).
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning dough once. Cover; let rise until double (1 1/4 hours).
Punch down; cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll to slightly less than 1/2-inch on lightly floured surface.
Cut with a 3-inch round cutter (re-roll edges).

title: fruit loop cookies
directions: *Use a little less sugar if using frosted cereal.

title: one-minute cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Boil 1 minute after mixture begins to boil.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine chopped vegetables with salt.
Let stand for 2 hours. Drain well.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Add drained vegetables and bring back to boiling point. Pack in hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: sauteed trout samuel
directions: Put shrimp in a large pot, cover with water (salt added) and boil until tender.
In a saucepan, saute mushrooms lightly.
Add pimentos, shallots and asparagus, then shrimp and water.
Bring to a boil.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Crush vanilla wafers fine.
Let margarine set out to room temperature.
Mix with wafers.
Press into 8 x 10-inch Pyrex dish. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: wonderful baked beans
directions: Combine
onion
and bacon in skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Stir
in
beans, syrup, chili sauce and mustard.
Heat until bubbly.
Reduce
the
heat;
simmer,
uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple roll
directions: Make a syrup of brown sugar and water by cooking 5 minutes. Pour into a deep baking dish.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into a bowl.
Cut in shortening and then add milk to make a dough.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and spread with chopped apples to which sugar, cinnamon and butter have been added.
Roll like a jelly roll and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place pieces in the hot syrup, cut side down, and bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen daiquiri
directions: Mix all together.
Keep in deep freeze until ready to use.

title: canned deer meat
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Put 1 teaspoon of mix in each pint jar.
Pack the jars tightly with meat.
Do not add water to the jars.
Pressure cook pints for 75 minutes on 11 pounds.
Cook quarts 90 minutes on 11 pounds.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break 1/2 angel food cake in small punch bowl.
Layer with 1/2 of each ingredient as listed, then repeat with the 1/2 remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine and mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Make meatballs golf ball size and place on a cookie sheet side by side.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: easy cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and egg until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Blend sour cream, vanilla and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pour over cream cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Chill well before serving.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix.
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 25 minutes.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Mix the first ingredients in small bowl.
In large bowl, mix milk and pudding, then blend in Cool Whip.
Combine with other ingredients.
Crush cookies; layer cookies, then cream in glass bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: christmas cranberry jello
directions: Peel banana and split lengthwise; do the same to both halves. Cut into small chunks on lettuce leaves, mound-like.
Grind the peanuts and sprinkle over the banana and put mayonnaise on the side to use as you wish.
Do not mix.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Thoroughly hand mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix chilies, soups, broth, 1 1/2 cups cheese and onion.
In 9 x 13-inch greased pan, layer Doritos, sauce and chicken; repeat. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with foil for the first 20 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: simple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Add flour. Bake 1 hour in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, then crumbs, reserving 1/3 cup for garnish.
Pat crumbs firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir in pie filling and fruit cocktail; pour over crust.
Top with Cool Whip and crumbs. Freeze 4 hours.
Remove 20 minutes before cutting.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Rinse and dice potatoes.
Dilute soup with milk.
Combine all ingredients and cover top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco bread
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In large mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, cornmeal and yeast.

In medium saucepan, combine remaining ingredients, except flour and chiles. Heat until warm. Add to flour mixture in bowl. Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium. Stir in chiles and remaining flour by hand. Knead on floured surface until smooth. Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 60 minutes. Punch dough down. Shape into loaf. Place in greased pan. Cover and let rise 30 to 45 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown. Remove from pan and cool.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Cream together butter or crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Line tube pan with waxed paper.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Reduce heat to 325° and continue to bake for 45 minutes more.

title: husband's delight(tomato soup cake)
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and egg.
Add dry ingredients to flour and add to creamed mixture alternately with tomato soup.
Beat until smooth.
Add raisins; stir until covered.
Bake in 8-inch cake pans or cupcake pans (18 to 24).
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix together crushed Oreos and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Mix the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
In another bowl, mix together pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Combine cream cheese and pudding mixtures; pour into Oreo crust.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Chill or freeze.

title: quick muffins
directions: Break egg in bowl and stir with fork.
Stir in milk and salad oil (or shortening).
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin cups 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, oleo and nuts in small bowl. Blend well. Pat into 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Bake 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water at 110°.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to yeast mixture.
Combine shortening, sugar and salt.
Add scalded milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg.
Add 2 cups whole wheat flour.
Beat until flour is moistened.
Add remaining white flour.
If using electric dough hooks, beat 4 minutes.
If kneading by hand, knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface and cover. Let rise until double.
Shape rolls.
Let rise until double again. Bake in 375° oven about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Can be put into refrigerator immediately after mixing for 1/2 day or more, before making into rolls.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Beat egg yolk lightly; add yolk to sour cream.
Melt butter on top of stove in a saucepan.
Add sour cream mixture to melted butter.
Add Parmesan cheese and heat thoroughly.
Do not burn. Pour mixture over cooked pasta.

title: sunny scalloped potatoes
directions: Toss potatoes, salt, flour and dash of pepper together.
Place in an 11 x 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Cube cheese; cook with milk over low heat until smooth.
Add bell pepper, chopped pimento strips and chopped onion to melted cheese. Mix and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: one of jen's favorite recipes
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in orange sherbet.
Mix in orange mandarin sections, crushed pineapple and marshmallows. Refrigerate mixture, stirring occasionally, until thick but not set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate until set (1 to 2 hours).
Garnish with extra mandarin sections and/or mint leaves. Can also be served as a dessert.

title: quick chicken and gravy
directions: Cover chicken with flour. Brown in hot oil until chicken is cooked. Add both soups. Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal and raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and using spoon, form balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These are soft cookies that get better the longer you have them.

title: cheery cherry cheese pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until firm. Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving. Refrigerate.

title: ham salad
directions: I use fat-free whipped dressing (by Weight Watchers) and a little pickle juice.

title: canned apples
directions: Cover with 10 cup sugar and 1 cup vinegar.
Let stand over night.
Cook down like preserves, and seal in sterilized jars. Can be used as preserves or for fried pies.
Good luck!

title: saucy prune cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil and sugar in large mixer bowl; mix well.
Mix buttermilk and soda in cup.
Sift flour, baking powder, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves into bowl.
Stir in pecans.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition.
Mix in prunes, prune juice and vanilla.
Spoon into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Invert onto serving plate.
Pour sauce over cake immediately.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Crumble biscuits in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish. Mix other ingredients and pour over biscuits. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add sprouts, onion and seasonings. Squeeze the juice of 1 lemon over the sprouts in pan.
Dice the lemon peel and add 1 to 2 teaspoons to pan.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mush
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add salt.
Slowly add cornmeal, constantly stirring (wire whisk works best).
Continue stirring, until cornmeal thickens, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and let simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Let cool. Quickly add flour to mixture.
Pour mush into an oiled loaf pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut 1/4-inch slices, coat with flour and fry in oil or fat until golden and crunchy crust is achieved, approximately 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour kraut
directions: Add all the vegetables and kraut together.
Combine oil, vinegar and water; heat until hot.
Pour over vegetables. Marinate well.
Keeps for long time in the refrigerator.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Stir together and refrigerate.
When set, spread top with Cool Whip.

title: mini cocktail pizzas
directions: Combine and cook slowly until cheese is melted. Spread on cocktail rye bread.
Bake at 375° until bread is browned.

title: peaches, cream and rice dessert
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, bring rice, milk, 1/2 cup sugar and salt to boil. Cook 15 minutes, stirring often. Combine eggs and almond extract. Blend some rice mixture into eggs, then gradually stir remaining mixture. Cook 1 minute or until mixture thickens. Spoon rice into greased oven-safe dish. Arrange peaches over pudding. Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar. Broil about 2 minutes until sugar melts. Top with sour cream. Mix brown sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over sour cream. Makes 6 servings.

title: texas beans
directions: Brown
ground beef; add onions and bacon.
Put in baking dish and
add
remaining
ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix water and Jell-O.
Chill until thick as an egg white.
Mix all other ingredients and add to Jell-O.
Congeal until firm.

title: cajun rice
directions: Cut or puree tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: quail or dove
directions: Remove all feathers and possible shot.
Wash and soak in salt water.
Drain.
In a paper bag, put flour, salt and pepper.
Add birds and shake until coated.
In an iron skillet, heat oil until hot.
Make sure oil partially covers birds.
Brown birds on both sides.
Remove cooked birds and pour off oil, reserving enough oil to brown sufficient flour to make gravy.
To the brown flour, pour in enough hot water to make a thin gravy.
Place birds in a roaster on a rack and pour the gravy over the birds.
Cover and roast at 375° for one hour.
Baste birds at intervals.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut meat in small pieces.
Cook until tender.
Remove and cool. Put V-8 or tomato juice with broth and add diced carrots, celery, cabbage and onion.
Cook until tender, approximately 30 minutes, then add potatoes (cut in small pieces) and noodles, if you like. Cook about 15 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add canned vegetables and shredded beef.

title: almost-instant pierogi
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain and return to pot.
Add cheese to hot potatoes and mash until potatoes are smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Add onions and cook 15 minutes until tender.
Heat oven to 350°. Have 2 (13 x 9-inch) baking dishes ready.
Spread half the onions over the bottom of baking dishes.
Stuff shells and arrange over onions.
Spread remaining onions over top.
Bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes until heated through.

title: burnt caramel icing
directions: Caramel:
Dissolve 1/2 cup sugar in a sizzling skillet.
Stir it until it browns to an amber color.
Add 1 cup hot water.
Stir until mixture dissolves into a thick syrup.
Makes 1/2 cup caramel.

title: sausage bread
directions: Mix 2 eggs, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add grated cheese to the mixture until pasty.
Spread cheese and egg mixture on rolled out dough.
Drain sausage and spread over mixture.
Roll into jelly roll shape.
Place on a lightly floured pan with seam on bottom and ends tucked under.
Lightly oil dough top.
(Do not make slits on top.)
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut finger chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Roll dough to fit bottom of ungreased baking pan of 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Marinate by sprinkling vinegar and seasonings over meat.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.
Place meat in broiler pan and brown at 350° for 1 hour.
Transfer to Dutch oven.
Slice onion over top of meat.
Mix drippings from browning pan with 1 can beer, 1/3 cup chili sauce and 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Add enough water to total 2 cups liquid.
Cover; bake at 325° for 4 hours.
Cool in liquid and refrigerate until cold.
Slice when cold.
When ready to serve, heat in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Gravy will be thin.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine vegetables with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Place remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Drain vegetables and add to vinegar mixture; stir gently.
Ladle into plastic freezer containers and freeze.
When ready to use, defrost and serve chilled.
Makes about 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cut up potatoes in 1-inch cubes.
Place onion over potatoes. Dilute soup with milk and pour over potatoes.
Cube Velveeta and place on top.
I use a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Mix all ingredients except the chocolate chips and paraffin together. Chill, then dip in a mixture of the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: In bowl cream sugar and butter.
Beat in vanilla and salt. Gradually stir by hand the flour until well blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Dough will be stiff.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork to 1 1/2-inch round.
Bake for 15 minutes or until light golden in a 350° oven.
While cookies are still warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In	large saucepan, blend soup, milk, mayonnaise, tuna, celery
and
onion	at low to medium heat.	Add cheese; stir until
melted.
Turn
off
heat; add noodles.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
If desired, top with crushed potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings. Terrific with a tossed salad and French bread!

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Heat all ingredients together in crock-pot or medium sauce pan on low, stirring occasionally. Serve with Wheat Thins, Triscuts or as a veggie dip. * I triple the recipe for large crowds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken breasts.
Cool.
Break up into small pieces.
Mix in bowl the celery soup, mushroom soup, macaroni, onion, cheese, milk and mushrooms.
Add chicken.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Pour mixture with chicken in pan and set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with bacon and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar jumbles
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together well.
Blend the flour, soda and salt together.
Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Take out before they look done.)
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: maraschino party cake
directions: Sift together cake flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add shortening, cherry juice, cherries and milk.
Beat 2 minutes by clock.
Add 1/2 to 2/3 cup unbeaten egg whites (4 large eggs). Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour batter into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: 2 minute microwave fudge
directions: Dump first 4 ingredients into a microwave container and cook on High for 2 minutes.
Mixture will not necessarily be mixed. Add the vanilla and nuts.
Stir everything until it is well mixed.

title: ham boats(makes 4 servings)
directions: Slice baked potatoes into halves lengthwise with paring knife. Gently scoop out the inside of the potato.
Mash potato centers with milk and sour cream.
Mix in ham, onion, and mustard. Put the shells on a serving plate.
Spoon the mashed potato mixture back into the shells.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of cheese on the halves. Microwave on 100% power for 2 minutes.
If cheese is not melted and potato not soft put back in on 100% power for 1 minute or two. Enjoy!

title: wedding salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk in double boiler.
Add jello and stir.
Blend in cream cheese, then add pineapple.
Chill until starting to set.
Add Dream Whip and salad dressing and blend well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
After chilled, cover with wrap.
Serves 24 to 28.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with graham crackers.
Cover with 1/2 pudding mixture.
Layer with graham crackers and add rest of pudding on top.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers.
Frost with can of milk chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: raspberry refresher
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend until light and frothy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bran flake cookies
directions: Cream together margarine (or oil) and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and banana, mixing well.
Add flour and remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons into crushed flakes.
Roll cookies until well coated.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Mix cake mix, orange slices and juice, vegetable oil and eggs thoroughly.
Pour well blended mixture into prepared pans.
Bake for 30 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Frost with pineapple icing.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown.
Drain. Stir in soup, vegetables and milk.

title: microwave vegetable stir-fry
directions: Put oil, ginger and garlic into a 2-quart microwave dish. Cook, uncovered, in microwave oven for 2 minutes at High.
Add onion, broccoli, cauliflower and pepper to casserole; stir.
Cover dish.
Cook in microwave 3 to 4 minutes at High or until vegetables are crisp.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: Mix well sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, ground cloves and baking powder and add to mixture. Beat all ingredients on low speed for 1 minute, then at medium speed for 1 minute.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely before serving.

title: chocolate almond bark
directions: Line 12 x 15-inch pan with foil and spray with vegetable spray.
Arrange crackers on foil.
Melt butter and brown sugar together.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes, cool slightly. Melt chips and spread over layer.
Sprinkle with nuts. Chill in refrigerator.

title: rita's bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs until light with fork.
Add sugar gradually and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Butter heavily 3 slices of bread and make sandwiches with 3 more slices.
Slice into quarters and line a casserole.
Pour egg-milk mixture over the buttered bread.
Add raisins and coconut and place in a pan of water.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: lower calorie granola
directions: Mix oats, wheat germ, dry milk and chopped nuts in a large bowl.
Heat and stir oil and honey in a small saucepan until blended.
Remove from heat and stir in cinnamon and vanilla. Drizzle honey mixture over oat mixture and stir thoroughly.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Remove and stir well.
Bake 10 minutes more; remove and stir.
Bake 5 minutes more. Cool completely.
Add raisins and store in an airtight container. Serving size:
1/4 cup.
Contains 155 calories per serving. Exchanges:
1 bread, 1 fruit and 1 fat.
Contains 30 mg. sodium.

title: grandma's sugar cookies(from mid 1920's)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add more flour, if needed, to thick consistency.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Press down and sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, applesauce, 1 cup coconut and eggs.
Blend; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Let cool, then pick with a fork all over the top.
Leave in pan.
Spread pineapple over top (do not drain).

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and debone chicken (reserve broth).
Add bell pepper, onion and celery to broth and cook until wilted, then add spaghetti.
While spaghetti is cooking, heat soups, Ro-Tel and Velveeta in saucepan; pour over drained spaghetti.
Put in a large baking dish and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
When done, sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing for at least 1 hour, turning occasionally.
When chicken is finished marinating, preheat oven to 350°.
One by one, shake excess dressing form each chicken breast and dredge breasts in seasoned bread crumbs.
Place chicken on a baking sheet that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sheran's hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in large container until ready to use. Put 3 tablespoons of mix to cup of hot water.
Marshmallows may be added.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Mix together dry pudding, juice and cinnamon.
Add cut up Granny Smith apples (6 apples).
Stir thoroughly.
Pour in bottom crust.
Dot with cholesterol-free butter.
Put on top crust.
Bake until done.

title: scalloped broccoli
directions: Cook
broccoli
according
to
package
directions (one bunch fresh
broccoli,
about 1 1/2 pounds cooked and drained, may be substituted
for
frozen).
Place broccoli in 10 x 6 x 2-inch shallow baking dish.
Blend soup, milk and cheese; pour over broccoli.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Lift out vegetables. Set aside.
Stir flour and salt into skillet.
Add half and half. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; blend in skillet mixture.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add chicken, vegies and pimento.
Serve with rice or biscuits.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and cube 8 medium potatoes.
Add celery and onion to potatoes.
Then combine dressing mix with mayo and water.
Add to potato mixture and toss to coat.
Chill and serve.

title: noodle doodle
directions: Prepare noodles as directed on package.
Add soup, peas, celery, pepper, pickle and mayonnaise.
Mix well and chill.
Good for picnics.
Add mayonnaise just before serving.

title: sauce amandine
directions: In
heavy
skillet,
melt
butter
and	margarine.
Add almonds and
saute until lightly browned, stirring occasionally. Stir in
garlic, lemon juice
and wine.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook
until sauce bubbles, stirring with a wooden spoon. Serve sauce over broiled or grilled fish or shellfish. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: steak and vegetable stew
directions: Kill and carefully pluck 2 adult Spam. Place on pine board and cover with oregano, ramps and 2 sprigs parsley. Place Spam and pine board in oven; bake for 2 hours at 375°.
Remove pine board and rake off Spam into trash. Board may be eaten after cooling.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: In a large bowl, melt caramels in a microwave.
Add cream cheese; stir until smooth.
Then add marshmallow cream.
Stir until smooth.
Refrigerate until cool.
Dip sliced apples into, or pour over.

title: baked chicken with mushrooms
directions: Line a large baking pan with aluminum foil.
Place mushrooms in a baking pan.
Place chicken pieces on top of mushrooms.
Add lemon pepper seasoning.
Slowly pour Butter Buds mixture over chicken.
Fold aluminum foil over chicken and seal.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to this the shortening, milk, vanilla and eggs. Beat until smooth.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch layer pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mamma's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cool.
Remove the bones and place chicken in a baking dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dressing on top of soup mixture. Melt margarine and pour over dressing.
Brown top of casserole. Then pour broth over it and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: perfect chicken casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole dish, blend soup and milk; stir in chicken, eggs and peas.
Bake at 450° for fifteen minutes.
Top with chips and bake for 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix meats, cracker crumbs, eggs, milk and pepper. Shape into loaf. Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barley thickened mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour; continue cooking until browned.
Add water gradually with milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Stir frequently; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or
until barley is tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Make in a large flat casserole dish or pan.
Layer in order.

title: golden gate dressing
directions: Combine and chill 1 hour.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve over fruit.

title: texas hash
directions: In a large frying pan, saute onions and peppers in oil, about 5 minutes.
Crumble ground beef into pan.
Add salt and stir; when mixture begins to thicken, add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce. Cook on slow heat; then add rice.
Simmer, covered, about 10 minutes.

title: peking roast
directions: First cut crisscross slits deep down into the roast; trim off all fat.
Place roast in very hot skillet with melted butter. Brown well on all 4 sides.
After slicing onion into long pieces, push them down into the slits.
Place roast in a large bowl and pour the vinegar over and down into the slits.
Leave roast overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, pour off vinegar. Place roast in a large stew pan.
Pour the black coffee over it, then add water until roast is covered. Cover pan and cook at medium heat for 4 hours.
One half hour before done, season to your taste.
Gravy may be eaten, if desired. Roast will be very tender.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Dip chicken in sauce and put in foil-lined pan.
Pour remaining sauce over meat; bake for 15 minutes at 500°.
Reduce to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes super pork chops, too!

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown and drain beef and sausage.
Place in crock-pot on low. Add Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom soup; cut up Velveeta into square chunks.
Stir periodically.

title: rice and pigeon peas with pork
directions: In a large saucepan, add oil and brown meat.
Add onion, garlic and cilantro.
Let it simmer for about 2 minutes.
Add red bell peppers, green olives, chicken bouillon cubes, tomato sauce, Sazon, pigeon peas, salt and pepper.
Let simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add the rice and water; mix real well.
Bring to a boil and let the water evaporate.
Mix it again.
Cover and cook over a low flame for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese. Then add all other ingredients.
Place in freezer for 30 minutes and serve.

title: peach sauce
directions: Cook sugar, egg, flour and water until thickened.
Add vanilla and butter.
When cool, add chopped peaches.
Serve over ice cream or cake.

title: old fashioned honey  bread
directions: Mix 1 -1/2 cups of the flour, salt, honey, margarine and yeast in large bowl.
Add the very warm water.
Beat by hand for two minutes.
Beat in egg.
Stir in enough of the remaining, 1/2 cup at a time, to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead about 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place about 1 hour or until double in size. Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.
Grease bottom and side of pie plate with shortening.
Punch down dough.
Shape dough into a ball.
Place in pie plate; flatten slightly.
Mix egg white and water; brush on top of loaf.
Sprinkle with oats.
Cover and let rise in warm place 45 to 60 minutes or until double.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake about 35 minutes or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped and is golden brown.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: In a casserole dish, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together until partially blended (mixture is too stiff to thoroughly blend in all of the dry ingredients).
Put margarine over top in the center of the mixture.
Microwave on High 1 minute or until milk feels warm on bottom of dish.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
If all of the margarine has not melted in cooking, it will melt as you stir the mixture.
Pour into a dish that you have greased with 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Place in freezer.
Clean the kitchen!
The fudge should be ready to eat now.
Don't make yourself sick; you can save some for tomorrow! You may have to use a spoon to eat it.
You may fix some ice water also.

title: pam crawford's fruity pizza
directions: Prepare as directed and bake on pizza pan.
Cool.
(You can spread it on cookie sheet with hands.)

title: no fuss rice meatballs
directions: Combine rice (right from box) with beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Mix lightly.
Shape mixture into 1 1/2 inch balls; place in skillet.
Mix remaining juice, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder; pour over meatballs.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 40 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add chocolate.
Alternate milk, flour and vanilla.
Add water.
Bake at 375° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: jennifer's reunion casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef, sausage and onion.
Drain fat. Stir in 1 cup cheese, green pepper, corn, soup, tomato sauce, garlic, salt and noodles.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to boil and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in powdered sugar; beat until smooth.
Spread into buttered 9-inch square pan or dish.
Chill.

title: tuna and macaroni casserole(yummy and easy!)
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Rinse and drain thoroughly.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Blend in 2 tablespoons of flour.
Stir milk in slowly; heat to simmering, being careful not to burn.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cooked noodles in shallow buttered baking dish. Stir in soup and tuna.
Mix well; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven or 10 minutes in microwave.

title: calaloo
directions: Boil codfish twice.
Pick apart with hand.
Put spinach in frying pan with oil, then add bacon, tomatoes and onion.
Saute. When onion is cooked, add codfish and cook for 5 minutes, stirring all the time.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal with sugar, flour, soda and salt in large bowl. Add beaten eggs, shortening and buttermilk. Mix well. Store in refrigerator. Use as desired. Fill muffin tins and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Will keep 6 weeks.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine flour and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar in bowl; mix well.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press into greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar, baking powder, lemon juice and salt in mixer bowl; beat well.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until set.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.

title: 3 layer pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, melted butter and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake.
Cool before adding next layer.

title: leek salad
directions: Cook the leeks in the minimum of boiling salted water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Place in deep serving dish.
Mix together the remaining ingredients with salt and pepper to taste and pour over leeks.
Leave to marinate for at least 1 hour in the refrigerator.
Then sprinkle with a little paprika to add colour (color) just before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Cream together cheese and powdered sugar.
When smooth, cream in peanut butter, then fold or mix on low speed Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots (do not overcook) and drain while hot.
Slice onions and peppers.
Pour on carrots while hot.
Mix other ingredients and add to carrots.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Set in slightly warm place for 2 hours.
Knead slightly.
Roll out with hands.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Spread with butter and fold over.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These freeze well.
Just set out to thaw for a few minutes before baking.

title: saucepan oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil 3 minutes.
Stir in oats and peanut butter.
Return to stove; bring to boil.
Remove from heat; stir until slightly thickened.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool.
Yields 36.

title: jo anne erkert's swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving sized pieces.
Flour steak and brown in a pan with the sliced onions.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 3 hours.
Remove lid for last 45 minutes to thicken.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Dip refrigerated balls in chocolate mixture; drain and remove toothpicks.
Place on waxed paper.

title: low calorie drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in order in blender.
Blend on low speed until smooth.
Serve with half bagel.
One serving=1 1/2 cups, 210 calories, 1 gram fat.

title: poor boy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Last ten minutes, top with one can of biscuits.
Top biscuits with one strip of cheese.
Finish baking until biscuits are browned.

title: lady fingers
directions: Add ingredients in order (except for powdered sugar). Shape a small amount in rectangle about the size of your pinky finger. Bake 8 - 10 minutes at 375°. Roll in powdered sugar when cooled.

title: tallerina
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Cook noodles until tender.

title: spicy seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store, covered, in airtight container.
Shake before using to blend.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Add soup, milk, broccoli and jalapeno Cheez Whiz in soup pot.
Simmer on low to medium heat until broccoli is tender and Cheez Whiz has melted.

title: lanee's cheese potatoes(microwave)
directions: Slice potatoes 1/2-inch thick (round).
Place in microwavable bowl.
Cover with water.
Cook on High 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain water. Layer potatoes, then cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish. Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Pour milk over top.
Place in microwave until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: honey walnut bread
directions: Mix milk and honey over heat until blended.
Beat in butter, eggs, flour, salt and baking powder until well mixed.
Fold in nuts.
Put in ungreased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Cool before slicing.
Divine.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix soup and water.
Add rice, celery and onion.
Add broccoli, bits of butter and Cheez Whiz.
Mix all together in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup hot water and add remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; add vanilla and salt after chocolate is melted.
Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten egg yolks.
Add 3/4 cup of buttermilk alternately with sifted flour. Dissolve soda in remaining 1/4 cup of buttermilk.
Add to cream mixture.
Stir in chocolate; fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cookie bars
directions: Mix both sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add salt, vanilla and soda water mix, then add flour and mix. Add 1 package of chocolate chips and coconut to desired amount.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in skillet.
Add sausage, 2 1/4 teaspoons of cornstarch, dash of pepper, 1 1/2 tablespoons of brown sugar and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly until pork has lost all reddish color.
Transfer meat mixture to bowl and set aside.

title: tim's peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter. Blend until appearance is that of biscuit mix. Spread over half of the mixture on pie shell. Combine white sugar, salt and cornstarch; add scalded milk and mix well. Pour small amount

over beaten egg yolks and mix well, then return to milk mixture. Cook in top of double boiler until mixture thickens. Add butter and vanilla. Pour mixture into pie shell. Top with meringue and sprinkle remainder of peanut butter mixture on the top. Baked at 325° until the meringue is brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place the sliced cucumbers, onions and peppers in a large container. Sprinkle with salt. Add ice and cover.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well. Add remaining ingredients.
Place over low heat.
Keep turning pickles over until mixture reaches the scalding point.
Do not boil.
Bottle while hot in jars and seal. Let stand 48 hours before eating.
Yields 8 pints.

title: brownies
directions: Mix the sugar and eggs together. Add oil. Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Coat with a thin layer of chocolate icing.

title: zippy crisp chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush chicken with salad dressing. Coat with combined crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix together and let dry for 1 hour.
Spread out and dry further (time depends on the weather).
Store in a tight container.

title: pan potato sausage
directions: Mix all together; put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover until brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix flour, soda and sugar; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast and mix together.
Let rise 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll out and bake until done.
Cook at 400° until brown.
This dough keeps for several weeks.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Yield:
9 quarts or approximately 45 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: warm mushroom salad
directions: Rinse mushrooms and dry.
Cut each in half.
In a large skillet, saute mushrooms and pepper in oil 6 minutes until vegetables are lightly browned and tender.
Meanwhile, remove and discard stems from spinach; wash and dry well.
Place in serving bowl; stir vinegar and mustard into skillet.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Toss with spinach.
Makes 4 servings.

title: autumn soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook and stir onions with meat until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tomatoes, heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes longer.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, cream together the sugar and shortening. Add eggs, vanilla and salt. In second bowl, mix soda with some milk, then add 1 cup diced rhubarb. Add to sugar mixture. Blend together well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
In second bowl, mix together other half of the rhubarb, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Spoon over top of cake. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sauerkraut lasagna
directions: Boil and mash potatoes with a little oleo; add about 1/2 of cheese.
Boil noodles and drain.
Saute onions in remaining butter. Put layer of onions and butter (oleo) in baking pan.
Then add layer of noodles, kraut and then potatoes, onion, oleo, noodles, kraut, potatoes and end with onions and oleo and sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Remove any unpopped kernels of popcorn.
Add nuts.
In saucepan, bring brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt to a boil.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Turn off heat, quickly stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Gently combine with popcorn and nuts.
Divide mixture between 2 oiled 9 x 12-inch pans.
Place in 250° oven and bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately spread out onto wax paper to cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together grated cheese, green pepper, onion and pimento and set aside.
