Add sour cream, corn meal, milk, creamed corn, oil and eggs.
Pour meal mixture in half.
Pour in cheese mixture, then other half of meal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry pineapple crunch
directions: Put pineapple and cherry pie filling in cake pan.
Mix together melted butter and cake mix.
Pour over filling.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine raisins and pineapple; let set overnight.
Beat together the first 2 ingredients.
Stir in bran cereal; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt; blend in brown sugar.
Add bran mixture, stirring just until combined.
Add pineapple-raisin mixture.
Fill greased muffin pan cups 2/3 full. Bake in a preheated hot oven (400°) for 18 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cranberry candy
directions: Melt cranberry sauce in pan.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add gelatin.
Mix until smooth.
Let stand 20 minutes, then add chopped walnuts. Pour in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and let stand 24 hours.
Cut in squares and roll in sugar.
Do not refrigerate.

title: museli(delicious morning starter)
directions: Cover with distilled water and refrigerate overnight.
Grate a small apple into a bowl.
Spoon in Museli.
Top with a dollop of yogurt.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain diced pineapple, mixed fruit and mandarin oranges and set aside.
Blend sugar, flour and salt in small bowl and set aside.
Blend lemon juice, pineapple juice and 1 egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Cook until thick in a double boiler.
Chill.
Beat whipping cream until fluffy and stiff.
Add to cooked mixture. Fold in fruit and marshmallows.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange. Mix with sugar and let stand overnight.
Dissolve jello in warm water. When half set, add to first mixture. Add nuts, apples, marshmallows, celery and pineapple.
Let set.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Crush and whip bananas very light.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda and nuts.
Alternate the bananas and flour. Turn into a greased and floured loaf pan and bake in a 325° oven until done.

title: play dough(recipe for children)
directions: Mix together on low heat until desired consistency (may be colored with food coloring).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Cook and drain sausage.
Line dish with bread crumbs. Sprinkle sausage and cheese over bread.
Pour eggs and milk mixture over this.
Cover with plastic and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cocoa in saucepan.
Add milk and butter to pan and bring to boil. Add vanilla. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter, oatmeal, coconut and nuts. Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: holiday apple pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry; arrange apples in pie plate. Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Sprinkle mixture over top of apples.
Dot with butter.
Bake in preheated oven of 425° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook chopped spinach as per directions on package.
In heavy skillet, cook with butter the sliced bacon or chopped ham, the onion, bell pepper and pimiento.
Cook until crisp and golden. Drain well, then cover bottom of pie, spreading the already-sauteed ingredients.
Put it in the oven to cook the pie crust a little.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies until you have coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
To rest, add melted butter.
Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cheese with electric mixer; add powdered sugar and beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on crust.
Let chill 30 minutes.
Mix pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese layer; chill 1 hour.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chill one hour.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Heap up in a pastry-lined pan.
Dot with 1-1/3 Tbsp butter. Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425 for 50 to 60 minutes.
Bake until crust is nicely browned and apples are cooked through.
Serve warm or cold.
May be topped with cream, whipped cream, or ice cream.

title: yummy broccoli
directions: Arrange broccoli in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake covered, at 350° for 1/2 hour. Yields 6 servings.

title: peanutty double chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets or line with parchment.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl until blended.
Add eggs, baking soda and vanilla; beat until light. Blend in flour and peanut butter until dough is stiff and firm. Stir in chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Drop dough by teaspoons 2 inches apart onto cookie sheets.
Press cookies down with tines of a fork to flatten slightly.
Bake 12 minutes or until just barely done, do not overbake.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix everything together except the bread and chill for at least 2 hours.
Take the bread and cut the middle out of the bread.
Break middle piece into bite size chunks.
When ready to serve, place the chunks around the outside of the bread and fill center of hollowed bread with the dip.
Dip chunks into dip.

title: grandma westermeyer's fruitcake
directions: Bring the sugar, water and raisins to a boil and simmer about 5 minutes. Add 1 tsp. shortening while hot. Cool. Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together. Mix with cooled raisin mixture. Add a generous cup of walnuts and divide between 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325 degrees for one hour.

title: yum-yum pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add pineapple and mix well.
Stir in pie filling and food coloring.
Cook over medium heat until thickened (5 to 8 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in dry gelatin.
Let cool, then stir in bananas and spoon into pie shells.
Cover with whipped topping and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate until pie is set.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together the flour, salt and baking powder with water until sticky.
Roll out on floured surface.
Slice and drop in boiling broth; do not stir.
Place lid on and put on simmer for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Add first egg, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Mix well.
Press mixture into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix cottage cheese and second egg.
Spread over crust.

title: pennsylvania dutch corn fritters
directions: Add corn to well beaten egg yolks.
Stir in flour and seasoning.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Heat shortening until very hot in a large skillet and drop corn mixture by spoonfuls.
Turn to brown both sides.
Serve hot.

title: as you like it casserole
directions: The options that make it as you like it:
Onion, 1 clove garlic, green or red pepper, drained can of kidney beans, drained can of mushrooms or use a spaghetti sauce with these ingredients.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and 2 cups sugar thoroughly.
Mix Wesson oil, nuts, eggs, vanilla, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together and mix with apples and sugar.
Put in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Crush pretzels (not fine); add oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar. Mix well until moist and place in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 275°.
Cool.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add frozen strawberries and stir until dissolved.
Soften cream cheese; beat with 1 cup sugar until fluffy and fold in Cool Whip.
Put cream cheese mixture over crust.
Pour jello mixture over cheese. Chill until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix cream cheese, bell pepper, onion, salt and pineapple together.
Shape into ball.
Coat with chopped pecans.
Chill 3 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok over moderately high heat.
Add onion and zucchini.
Stirring frequently, cook until onion is lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Remove vegetables with slotted spoon and set aside.
Add remaining oil to wok along with carrots, peas and beans.
Cook 5 more minutes, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to moderate.
Add water, currants, salt, curry powder and soy sauce.
Cover, stirring occasionally, and continue cooking until beans are crispy and tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in onion and zucchini that had been set aside.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more. Serve over brown rice and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jalapeno cheese spread
directions: Tangy and keeps indefinitely; great for stuffed celery.

title: makeover peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixing bow, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix in peanut butter and sugar.
Gradually add milk; mix well. Gently fold in whipped topping. Spoon into the crust.
Refrigerate overnight. Yield:
8 slices.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions for 1st layer.

title: trade wind salad
directions: Melt margarine with brown sugar in large skillet.
Add cubed lunch meat.
Cook and stir until golden brown.
Cook macaroni. Mix cooked meat, cooked macaroni, pineapple, cheese and green pepper in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream (or yogurt), pineapple juice and salt together well.
Add to meat and macaroni mixture.
Mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce if desired.

title: cardamon dressing
directions: In small bowl with mixer at low speed, beat all ingredients until mixed.
Increase speed to medium.
Beat until smooth.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with fruit.

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas on bottom of crust.
Spoon ice cream on top. Freeze 2 hours.
Top with unbeaten fudge sauce, pineapple, whipped cream, nuts and cherries.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite sized pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and add broth or water to make the consistency that you want.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes in a 9x12 covered baking dish.

title: broccoli-peanut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water until tender.
Drain broccoli. Mix egg, mayonnaise, cream of mushroom soup, 1/2 cup grated cheese, grated onion and chopped peanuts in with broccoli.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in greased casserole bowl for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Melt in top of double boiler or microwave, the morsels, milk, and butter, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir until thoroughly blended.
In large bowl, combine nuts, marshmallows, and chocolate mixture.
Spread in wax paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan, peel off paper, cut into squares. Cover and store at room temperature.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Beat sauce until smooth.
Stir in orange and lemon juice. Pour cranberry mixture over ice cubes in punch bowl.
Resting bottle on rim of bowl, carefully pour in ginger ale.
Makes 25 (5 ounce) servings.

title: mushroom-stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Bake at 425° until soft.
Cut a slice off top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out pulp into a bowl reserving 1/4-inch layer inside.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in small skillet.
Add mushrooms, saute for about 5 minutes.
Mash potato pulp with remaining margarine.
Add half and half, onion powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Beat until fluffy (add more milk if needed).
Stir in mushrooms.
Heap mixture in potato shells. Arrange on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Peel and grate zucchini.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and finish cooling.

title: english truffle cake
directions: Drain cherries; reserve some cherry juice for color at the end.
Add rum to cherries and let set about half hour before using.
Tear angel cake into bits in a large bowl .
Make vanilla pudding according to directions on package.
Mix cake, pudding and 1 cup of the cherries, drained.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Whip heavy cream; add bit of cherry juice for color.
Top with whipped cream; decorate with remaining 1 cup cherries on top of cream.
Let stand in refrigerator to blend flavors.

title: crabmeat ball
directions: Beat the first 2 ingredients together; make into a ball.
Just before serving, pour ketchup and horseradish over ball.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Stir in alternately with sour cream.
Mix together sugar, chips and cinnamon.
Pour 1 layer of batter, then a layer of chip mixture, then another layer of batter.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Bring to boil over low heat.
Wrap 1/2 bacon slice around a water chestnut and secure with toothpick.
Bake bacon wrapped chestnut at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until done.
Use broiler pan to catch bacon drippings.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Cook noodles according to directions on box, drain.
In large skillet, brown meat and onions, stir in tomatoes, chili powder and salt.
Heat through. Combine with noodles.
Pour into a three quart casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: crack-top ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in molasses and egg.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Then form into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix brown sugar, powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla until well blended.
Put into a serving dish and sprinkle chopped peanuts over top.
Serve with apples for dipping.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: cheesy lemon bars(or chocolaty chocolate bars)
directions: Combine cake mix,
butter
and	1
egg.
Pat
into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Blend lemon juice or buttermilk, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add	2
eggs and beat 3 to 5 minutes. Spread over base.
Bake
at
for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: sugared yams
directions: Heat water, pineapple juice and sugar together.
Add margarine and nutmeg.
Peel and slice sweet potatoes in thick slices.
Drop into boiling syrup.
Cover and let simmer until tender and transparent.

title: country ham casserole
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add shredded cheese.
Cook cauliflower florets slightly; mix with ham and white sauce.
Put melted butter and crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Don't overcook cauliflower.

title: refrigerator cheese cookies
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter and beat in the sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together and gradually work into creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth.

title: bacon, egg and cheese casserole
directions: Do anything to taste; you can't mess this one up!

title: 12-month refrigerated tomatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in a gallon glass jar and refrigerate.
Can half the recipe.
Will keep 12 months refrigerated.
Good with dry beans.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Last 10 minutes top with 1 1/2 cups cornflake crumbs, mixed with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/2 c. melted margarine and 1 egg.
Mix well and pat into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Mix the pumpkin, brown sugar, spice,
2 eggs and milk together.
Pour over crust.

title: fritos pie
directions: Heat chili in saucepan.
Put Fritos in casserole dish.
Pour chili over Fritos.
Slice cheese and lay on top of chili.
Place in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: great chicken and rice casserole
directions: Wash and pat dry the chicken pieces; discard the gizzard, heart and liver.
Place the pieces in a 9 x 13-inch roasting pan. In a mixing bowl, whisk together the rice, the veloute or soup, water and onion soup mix.
Pour rice mixture over chicken.
Place pan in oven and bake approximately 1 hour.
When finished, the casserole will have a brown crust.
Remove the casserole and let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in 3 cups boiling water.
Add broccoli and cook until crisp-tender.
Saute butter and onion. Add flour.
Stir in half and half; stir constantly until thick. Add broccoli with water into pot with flour mix.
Stir until well mixed and cook just a minute or two more.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes about 6 bowls.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems and chop fine.
Place mushroom caps on paper towel.
Microwave on Medium-high for 3 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Microwave bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Add mushroom stems, onion, salt, pepper and red pepper sauce. Microwave on High until mushrooms and onion are tender (2 to 3 1/2 minutes).
Blend in flour; stir in cream until smooth.
Microwave on Medium-high 2 to 3 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking time.
Stir in cheese.
Fill each cap with bacon/mushroom mixture.
Place on microwave-safe plate and microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Rotate plate 1/2 turn.

title: microwave chocolate almond pie
directions: Break chocolate bar into small pieces in a large microwaveable bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until chocolate is melted.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker pie shell.
Freeze 4 hours until firm.
Serves 6.
Very good.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes and place in large baking dish.
Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in margarine.
Mix tomatoes and melted cheese with onion mixture.
Pour over potatoes.
Heat at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: tuna bunwiches
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Separate the biscuits and roll out on floured board. Roll into 5 x 3-inch ovals.
Spoon tuna mixture onto 4 ovals. Top with 4 ovals.
Moisten edges and seal by pressing edges with fork.
Cut desired shapes from remaining ovals to make decorations for tops of sandwiches. Brush surface with 1 beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put
popped corn in a large brown paper bag; put pecans on top of corn.
On stove, cook sugar, butter and syrup until it turns from
yellow
to
caramel gold color, about 10 to 15 minutes. Stir
occasionally.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour
over popcorn.
Fold
bag
top
and microwave 1 1/2 minutes on
High. Take
out
and
shake
hard.
Repeat 2 more times.

title: boiled okra
directions: Wash okra.
Remove tops, leaving on part of pod to keep juices inside.
Cover with water.
Add salt and bacon drippings.
Boil until all water is gone.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil and cook 1 minute. Add coconut flavoring. Brush over cake while still hot.

title: boursin cheese ball
directions: Mix together and chill.
May be frozen into balls any size you prefer.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion and celery in bacon grease.
Add okra and cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and baking powder; stir well.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 or 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: baked chicken wings
directions: Split chicken wings in 2 sections.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat until sugar and butter dissolve.
Cool and pour over wings.
Marinate for 2 hours, turning occasionally, without removing sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, turning over once and spooning sauce over chicken a couple of times.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot.

title: old fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine chicken, onion, salt, pepper and about 6 cups water in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth; cool.
Bone chicken.
If necessary, add additional water to broth to measure 6 cups.
Return chicken to broth and bring to a boil.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and melted margarine, then add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Combine coconut to mixture.
Pour into pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Heat to boiling sugar, milk and caramels and boil 4 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add chocolate chips, vanilla and salted peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: brisket barbecue
directions: Brown brisket on both sides on grill.

title: layered squash casserole
directions: Arrange in layers:
1st Layer:
Carrots and 4 crumbled saltines. 2nd Layer:
cream cheese. 3rd Layer:
Mix squash with can of cream of chicken soup and spread over cream cheese. 4th Layer: Grated onion and beaten egg. 5th Layer:
4 crumbled saltines, dots of butter on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: bundt like coffee cake
directions: Sift all the flour 6 times.
Keep 1/2 cup flour aside after sifting.
Then add baking powder to this.
Sift and set aside. Make a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks singley and beat.
Add flour, milk and vanilla alternately.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add the 1/2 cup flour mixture to batter, then fold in the egg whites. Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Alternate batter in layers with cinnamon mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Let cool 10 minutes in the pan, then remove from the pan and cool on the rack.

title: carrot cream soup
directions: In 4 quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add carrots and stir in flour, mixing well. Cook, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes.
Stil stirring, add chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and cook 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Blend in cream, add salt and pepper to taste and serve immediately.
Makes 12 cups.

title: american crisp cookies
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients.
Roll dough into 2-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pat down and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: flour tortilla pizza
directions: Brown meat and onion together.

Salt to taste until cooked. Lay flour tortilla flat open on cookie sheet; spread tomato sauce. Add 4 tablespoons meat, spread over sauce, then sprinkle both type of cheeses over meat and place in oven at 350° for about 5 to 10 minutes for cheese to melt, then serve.

title: baked chicken with potatoes
directions: Depending on how many you are cooking for, I usually use 6 chicken breasts and about 4 large potatoes.

title: beef porcupine balls
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, rice, salt and pepper and form into balls.
Fry in Dutch oven until light brown.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and water; cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower shrimp salad
directions: Slice the cauliflower, celery and onion.
Drain the shrimp. Combine all the ingredients and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Whip butter and Crisco until well blended.
Add sugar.
Beat until well blended. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add small amount of flour and a small amount of cream (4 parts flour and 3 parts cream).
Preheat oven at 325° and bake 1 hour.

title: fruit salad mold
directions: Place pie filling and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O; mix well.
Let cool a few minutes.
Pour into a bowl and cool until almost cold.
Add other ingredients and place into a mold or bowl.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stuff chilies with cheese strips.
Process in blender the flour, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture.
Grease casserole dish and place stuffed chilies in dish.
Spoon mixture over chilies and bake 12 to 16 minutes or until set.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Combine cake flour and baking powder.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: campfire cooking frontier chicken wings
directions: Deep fry chicken wings for about 5 minutes in Dutch oven. Remove fried chicken wings from oil and let oil drip off. Sprinkle mixed seasonings liberally over the chicken wings. Serve while still hot.
Eat warm.
Makes 12 to 16 wings.

title: baked fish in microwave
directions: Empty seasoned coating mix into plastic bag.
Dip fillets in melted margarine.
Shake 1 or 2 pieces at a time in bag until evenly coated.
Place on roasting rack which has been sprayed with Pam.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and cornstarch.
Beat eggs, milk, margarine and vanilla, then add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: maple walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Combine flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Combine buttermilk and maple syrup.
With an electric mixer set at medium-low speed, beat 6 ounces butter (12 tablespoons) and the granulated sugar until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Beat in 1 teaspoon maple extract and the vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Reduce speed and beat in flour mixture in 3 parts, alternating with buttermilk mixture.
Stir in chopped walnuts.
Pour into prepared pans and bake about 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire rack.

title: amish bundt rolls
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients except biscuits. Mix well.
Grease tube Bundt pan.
Place half of syrup mixture in bottom of pan.
Place biscuits on end around tube pan.
Pour remaining syrup over top of biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: pastry
directions: Mix flour and shortening until crumbly.
Beat egg.
Add water and
vinegar
to egg.
Mix in with flour and shortening. Makes 4 to 5 pie crusts.

title: steak soup(for crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients except butter and flour in cooker.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
One hour before serving, turn to high.
Make a thickening of the butter and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Stir thickener into soup and cook on high until thickened.

title: peanut butter cracker cookies(no bake)
directions: Boil evaporated milk and sugar in saucepan 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir to blend.
Add crackers.
Beat and drop on waxed paper.

title: cherry pineapple salad
directions: Add all ingredients in order as listed.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: georgia peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons of butter. Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar. Cream remaining butter. Gradually add remaining sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla and mix well. Combine 2 1/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well. Dredge peaches with remaining 1/4 cup flour. Fold peaches into batter. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Let it cool completely before removing from pan.

title: low-fat banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients. Mix milk, egg whites, applesauce and bananas.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Fill paper muffin cups with batter and bake 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: jailhouse cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, covered, 20 to 25 minutes. With slotted spoon, remove carrots to a bowl.
Increase heat and bring to a rapid boil.
Reduce to glaze consistency.
Add carrots and coat evenly with glaze.
One 1 cup serving contains 95 calories and 0 gm fat.

title: marshmallow fudge bars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift dry ingredients and add. Mix well and add vanilla and nuts. Pour mixture into cake pan, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and cover with marshmallows, cut in half. Bake 3 more minutes, then spread and cool. Cover with your favorite frosting. Double recipe for cookie sheet pan.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large mixing bowl.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients (can add cauliflower).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp and macaroni casserole
directions: Boil macaroni for 15 minutes in salted water.
Drain and put in buttered casserole with shrimp.
Make white sauce by melting butter with flour.
Add milk slowly.
Add grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over macaroni in casserole.
Add pieces of cheese and dot with butter on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Grease a tube pan and heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except walnuts and cherries, very well.
Mix in 1/2 of the walnuts.
Spread cherry halves and remaining walnuts on bottom of the pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until done. Pour sauce over cake while it is still hot.
Remove from pan when totally cooled.

title: cherry salad(pink salad)
directions: In medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients and mix thoroughly, then fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: buttered broccoli and mushrooms
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Wash mushrooms, trim ends and slice 1/4-inch thick, through caps and the stems.
Saute the mushrooms in hot butter in medium skillet until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper; toss lightly.
Return broccoli to skillet; mix well.
Remove from heat.

title: pumpkin nuts
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a shallow pan at 250° until crisp and brown.
Stir occasionally.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir in potatoes. Bake at 400° until done.

title: german apple cake
directions: Pour eggs, oil and vanilla mixture into dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add and mix 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: First Layer:
Cream together the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar; mix until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip. Spread in crust.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown stew meat in a little oil and simmer in its own juice while chopping onion and bell pepper.
Add them to meat, along with chiles, tomatoes, water and garlic salt to taste.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Serve on flour tortillas.
(If desired, fresh chiles and tomatoes can be used, as well as fresh garlic and salt.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients very well in a large bowl.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or baking dish, which has been lightly greased. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not cover.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: friendship cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese, then top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve with flaky biscuits.

title: baker's 5 minute creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat sugar and milk into cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in Baker's coconut.
Fold in Cool Whip and almond extract.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving.
Quick, easy and good.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Stir in the Mazola and milk.
Drop small tablespoons onto the boiling stew.
Cover and boil gently for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and margarine until fluffy.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Beat well.
Add flour and beat until well blended.
Add crushed potato chips.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: nisu - finnish coffee bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on the warm water; let stand a few minutes; stir to blend.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, cardamon, eggs, and 2 cups flour.
Beat smooth.
Add 3 more cups flour, beat until smooth.
Stir in melted butter.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and turn greased side up.
Cover with damp towel and let rise in warm place until double in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down, cover and let rise again until almost doubled (1/2 hour). Turn out on lightly floured board.

title: durkee's chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a single layer in shallow baking dish.
Blend butter and Durkee's.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more until brown.
Serve chicken atop bed of rice.
Pour drippings over all.

title: orange cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat
all ingredients together with mixer and spread on cake.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in blender.
Let season 1 or 2 days.

title: baked honey mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange the chicken breasts in a single layer in baking pan. In a small bowl, stir together the ingredients. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until the chicken is cooked.

title: corn and potato chowder
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, stir soup, corn with liquid and milk over medium heat just to boiling.
Spoon into 4 bowls.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Beat pudding, milk and sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with oil.
Place whole graham crackers on bottom.
Top with 1/2 of pudding, then layer of crackers, remaining pudding, another layer of crackers and ice with can of icing.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Add sifted dry ingredients and vanilla.
Add rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans or 1 loaf cake pan.
Top with sugar and butter.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Very moist bread.
Freezes well.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Make sure they are well blended. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
(I use a melon cutter dipped in warm water.)
Refrigerate again.

title: super simple barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Great to use on ribs, chicken or chops.
Just brush on as any barbecue sauce.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots and onion.
Set aside.
Slice and dice chicken into small pieces.
If shrimp, dice into small pieces also. Using wok or fry-pan, add oil. Let it heat up.
Add garlic and chicken. Stir until cooked.
Slowly add vegetable mixture. Keep stirring until all is in the pan.
Cook for 4 to 6 minutes. Add soy sauce until the flavor you like, 2/3 cup or less.

title: bean corn salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Mix chopped vegetables. Add vinegar, oil, sugar and salt.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream flour and margarine.
Add 1 egg at a time and 1 teaspoon vanilla and/or nutmeg.
Whip real well.
Whipping a long time is the secret to this pie.
Pour into deep dish shell and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: leftover sauces
directions: Thin leftover gravy (you may want to add chicken or beef bouillon).
Add diced onions, celery and/or green peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Add chunked potatoes, carrots, cauliflower, broccoli or cabbage (not too much unless you enjoy a strong flavor) and a can of whole or crushed tomatoes.
Cook until veggies are done.
If adding meat, cook veggies until almost done, then add meat.
Serve. Leftover beef, turkey or chicken gravy can be thinned, seasoned with onions and celery, and noodles added.
Serve over or with mashed potatoes.

title: easy bake stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in buttered 3-quart casserole dish or roasting pan.
Bake, covered, for 4 hours at 325°.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Add the buttermilk, eggs and oil.
Mix and beat until well moistened.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen muffins.

title: tomato and rosemary soup
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add onion and saute until limp.
Add rosemary and flour and stir in well.
Add broth or stock and stir until smooth with a whisk.
Stir in the tomatoes, puree and sugar. Cook gently for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and strain through a sieve.

title: bacon and cheddar muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin pans.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese and bacon just until moist.
Fold in cheese and bacon.
Divide batter in muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: spiced olives
directions: Drain the olives, discarding juice. Return to jar. In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Pour over olives; close jar and refrigerate for 3 to 10 days, turning jar daily. Drain before serving. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: pralines
directions: Bring to a
boil
sugar,
milk, boiling water and white Karo syrup in a very large saucepan.
Add soda;	bring to boil again. Add pecans.
Stir
constantly, continuing to firm ball stage. Remove from heat
and beat until it thickens and loses shiny gloss.

title: use of leftovers
directions: Chop up or grind bacon or pork and celery.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce leaves as salad or as a sandwich with lettuce.

title: devonshire cream for strawberries
directions: Beat together in small mixer bowl or blender.
Double recipe if necessary.

title: kev's famous double meat chili
directions: In 2 pans brown and drain the meat.
Cube sirloin first.
In a large pot over low flame, combine chopped onion, green pepper and minced garlic.
Add meat, spices, beer and tomatoes.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours or until thick.
Add beans for 20 minutes to warm them and serve.
Enjoy!!

title: herb garlic stuffed chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Slice pocket in breasts and fill with divided portions of 1 package of Aloutte cheese with herbs and garlic.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and lightly brush on Dijon mustard.
Heat heavy skillet over high heat.
Place chicken in skillet on non-pocket side down and grill until golden brown (approximately 10 minutes).
Turn and grill on other side.
Cover chicken.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, lemon juice and grated rind; mix well and pour on crust.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain off some of the liquid from squash.
Leave about 1/4 cup per can.
Combine squash, soup, carrots, onion, pimento and sour cream.
Set aside.

title: lillian dodge's gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg, molasses and dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add hot water and beat until smooth.
Bake in greased shallow pan for 35 minutes in 325° to 350° oven.

title: adelaide's marmalade
directions: Put fruit through grinder.
In large pan add 12 cups water to fruit and soak overnight.
Save grapefruit seeds and soak separately.
Drain seeds and tie in cloth.
Add to fruit.
Boil all down to 1/2 volume (about 1 hour).
Add sugar.
Boil down to 1/2 volume.
Put small amount in saucer in refrigerator to check stiffness.
Put in jars and seal.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together.
Let raise.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, salad dressing and Velveeta cheese. Pour into 9 x 10 baking dish. Crumble Ritz crackers on top and pour melted butter on crackers. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: philly surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Melt margarine. Add flour and nuts.
Mix well. Spread mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in oven for 25 minutes. Let cool.
Beat the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together. Spread on top of crust. Make pudding according to package. Spread on last layer. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and garnish with nuts.
Chill until served.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: *Omit if taco seasoning has lots of onion.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1 inch pieces. Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in milk, sugar, flour, nutmeg and rhubarb in 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Layer with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: angel strawberry delight
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and whipped cream.
Remove 2 to 3 cups of this for use later.
Slice the strawberries, reserving 10 whole ones for decoration.
Add a little sugar to the sliced strawberries.
Divide the angel food cake in half.
Mix the sliced strawberries with the 2 to 3 cups of Cool Whip mixture.
Spread this on the middle layer of the angel food cake.
Replace the top layer of the cake.
Frost the cake with the remaining Cool Whip mixture.
Decorate the top of the cake with the whole strawberries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Very good with fried fish.

title: savory beef noodle bake
directions: Melt butter in skillet on medium heat.
Add ground chuck, brown lightly.
Stir in garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Blend in cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add green onions.
Place 1/3 of noodles in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread 1/3 cream cheese over noodles, top with 1/3 meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand well.
Pour into prepared 13 x 9-inch pan.
Use solid shortening to prepare pan (no oil).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef;
add taco seasoning.
Add to lettuce mixture and pour on 2 bottles mild taco sauce.
Mix.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Brown beef in skillet. Add rice, tomatoes, salt, pepper, chili powder and onions. Mix well, breaking tomatoes and meat in small pieces. Cook until boils good and some of the liquid has cooked out. Top with corn bread batter made from 1 cup mix. Bake at 425 degrees about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 12 3/4-inch baking pan.
Combine Bisquick and granulated sugar and cut in margarine.
Add walnuts and sprinkle over apple mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and salt.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks, vanilla and butter.
Cool until thick.
Pour into a baked pie crust and beat egg whites and brown.
Serve cool.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: First Step:
Mix together pecans, flour and oleo.
Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes only.

title: maco taco
directions: Crush Doritos and spread in baking dish, 8 x 8 pan.
Warm up refried beans; spread on top of crushed Doritos.
Spread salsa over beans.
Top next with shredded lettuce.
Spread sour cream over lettuce.
Top with grated cheese.
Best after refrigerated for 1 hour at least.

title: my favorite casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, green pepper and onion until meat is browned.
Add next 11 ingredients and mix well.
Then add noodles and stir well.
Pour into a large baking dish, cover and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes more.
Serves 14 to 16 people.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Combine with rice and remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: In a large bowl, combine peanut butter, honey and vanilla. Add next 3 ingredients. If mixture is too stiff, add 2 teaspoons boiling water. Roll into balls. Roll in nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fudge cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour, butter and sugar and beat to resemble crumbs. Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan or Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Boil butter and milk, then cool to room temperature.
Mix all together, gradually adding sugar.
Add vanilla last.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in water and boil until leaves come off easily. Mix: hamburger, onion, eggs, rice & 1 c. tomatoes. Salt & pepper to taste. Place meat mixture in cabbage leaves and roll them. Put them in a baking dish. Mix tomato sauce, 1 c. water and 1 c. of tomatoes. Pour over cabbage rolls. Cook for 1-1 1/2 hours covered at 350 degrees.

title: mud cookies
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter. When melted, add sugar and cocoa. Mix well. Add milk. Cook over medium heat until comes to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes or until mixture reaches soft-ball stage. Remove from stove; add oats, peanut butter and vanilla extract. Mix well. Spoon onto wax paper and let set. Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: creamy mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add mushrooms.
Cook until liquid is evaporated. Melt butter in large saucepan.
Whisk in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes without browning.
Whisk in milk.
Add seasoning.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook 5 to 8 minutes.

title: boiled cabbage
directions: Add all ingredients together except salt and sugar. Boil for 10 minutes in a covered saucepan. Add salt and sugar. Let sit for a few minutes, then serve.

title: pineapple mold salad
directions: Put jello in a bowl and add hot water.
Stir until dissolved. Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add jello mixture at low speed.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into small jello mold and refrigerator until firm.

title: quick and easy delicious biscuits
directions: Mix thoroughly; turn out on lightly floured board and roll out to about 3/8-inch.
Cut with cutter and bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until brown enough to suit you.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix milk, shortening and sugar; bring to a boil.
Cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in a little warm water and stir into first mixture.
Mix in 6 cups flour.
Let rise for 2 hours, then add remaining flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Knead well. Keep dough in refrigerator and form into rolls 2 hours before baking.
Cover and let rise in warm place.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt together. Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla; beat to mix well, then add the zucchini.
Add the dry ingredients to the mixture and mix well, then add 1 cup pecans or chopped walnuts and 1 cup of raisins. Pour into 2 greased and floured bread loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fruit tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, pecans and crumbs together in mixing bowl.
Melt butter.
Add egg and butter, mix well.
Put dough into ungreased 12 to 14-inch round pizza pan, work it, pat it, slap it, jump on it until you get it smoothed into the pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt, stirring well.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans and coconut.
Pour filling into unbaked crust; top with remaining pecans.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths and place in bowl with 3/4 of the cheese and all the sauce and toss.
Add any pizza fixings you desire.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan or dish, smooth out.
Do not pack down.
Top with remaining cheese and if you want, any remaining toppings and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cucumber salad 1
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Let stand for 10 minutes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients in order given. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve very cold.

title: layered ranchero dip
directions: Spread bean dip or refried beans on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Then mix sour cream, mayonnaise, taco seasoning mix and garlic powder together.
Spread over bean dip.
Sprinkle grated sharp cheese over the sour cream mixture.

title: potato and turkey salad
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in boiling salted water for 35 to 40 minutes.
Drain, peel and cut into chunks.
Brown bacon and crumble.
Cut turkey into 1/2-inch cubes and tomatoes into wedges. Slice scallions.
Combine all ingredients with 1 1/4 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Refrigerate if necessary, but for best flavor bring to room temperature before serving.

title: linguini with white clam sauce
directions: Soften garlic in oil.
Add all other ingredients; saute over low flame for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix with linguini and serve.

title: millie's scrumptious shrimp cocktail dip
directions: Mix together in blender.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Let soften 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with crackers, chips or veggies.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together (one at a time).
Make dough in rolls.
Cover with wax paper and chill.
Slice, put on slightly greased cookie sheet and bake until lightly brown at 325° to 350°.

title: linda's blueberry crumb cake(9 to 12 servings)
directions: Rinse and drain berries (use spaghetti colander).
Turn them out onto a towel.
Pat lightly to dry.

title: banoffi(dessert)
directions: Layer into shells round slices of bananas; put caramel dip over bananas, then Reddi-Wip.
Sprinkle pieces of crunch overall.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mixture should be very moist but not soupy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place on middle rack of oven.
Cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes until top is golden brown.
Serve warm with sauce.

title: watermelon cookies
directions: Mix margarine and shortening.
Add 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add 1 egg, milk, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat well. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix.
Cover.
Chill.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients then add oil. Beat until Smooth.
Bake at 350° until done (25-30 minutes) in large oblong pan or 2 layers.
Filling: 2nd half of strawberries, 1 box powdered sugar, 1 stick softened
oleo.Beat until smooth, pour over cooled cake.

title: mandarin orange pies
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Mix oranges and Cool Whip (reserve a few slices to top pies with).
Mix both mixtures together and pour into crust.
Let set up in refrigerator until firm.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder in bowl.
Cut shortening in. Add milk and egg and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful into boiling soup, or casserole or slightly salted boiling water; reduce heat. Cook 12 minutes, covered (don't peek).

title: eggplant croquettes
directions: Cook eggplant until tender in boiling salt water, then drain. Peel and mash it fine.
Add bread crumbs, egg, butter and seasoning.
Cool and form into croquettes.
Roll in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry until golden brown in hot fat.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spread mixture in an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until golden brown on top.
Cut into squares or wedges and serve warm.

title: church punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl over ice.
If too strong, you may add a little water for taste.

title: homemade jiffy cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown in 350° oven.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Cook all ingredients except pecans to 230° on candy thermometer. Add pecans and stir.
Pour out on waxed paper.
Break apart when cool.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, tomatoes, garlic and pepper until tender in microwave or oven.
Brown beef and onion.
Put vegetables in bottom of bowl.
Add ground beef and chicken soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Combine soup, tomatoes and chili powder.
Layer in casserole dish beginning with tortillas, then beans, then soup mixture.
Repeat layers and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend until creamy and enjoy!

title: beef patties with savory sauce
directions: Mix meat and water. Salt and pepper to taste.
Form 4 to 6 patties.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer 5 minutes. Broil meat 3-inches from heat 5 minutes. Turn.
Spread sauce over patties. Broil 5 minutes.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour three 9-inch round cake pans.
Mix the first 10 ingredients at low speed for about 2 minutes.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: veal, pork or chicken colbert
directions: Coat meat with flour; shake off excess.
Mix egg with water. Dip each medallion in egg mixture.
Mix crumbs with salt and pepper.
Dip egg coated meat in crumbs.
Put meat on a rack and dry for 20 minutes before cooking.
Saute medallions in oil or butter until golden brown on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Remove to plate and keep warm.
Saute mushrooms in same pan.
Deglaze pan with wine.
Add mushrooms and meat to wine.
Can be served over rice or pasta.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix thoroughly.
Put into 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
You may double the recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with strawberries or fresh peaches and Cool Whip.

title: turkey pie casserole
directions: Cook carrots, potatoes and onion until tender.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Place biscuits on top and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Stir 1 cup water with the sugar, cornstarch and grated lemon peel.
Cook, stirring constantly (or use double boiler) until it thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in 3 tablespoons butter and 3 tablespoons lemon juice. Yields 2 cups.
Makes 10 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well; roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press down with small glass or fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
No flour.

title: lemon velvet
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
May add ice cubes.
Blend.

title: chuck pot roast with potatoes
directions: Place meat in roasting pan.
Surround with potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with onion soup mixture.
Cover tightly.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all except shrimp.
Add shrimp last to prevent them from breaking apart.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with dip size Fritos.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Mix 3/4 cup of sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg yolks; beat well.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until mixture thickens and coats spoon.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Divide mixture in half.
To one half, add chocolate and vanilla. Mix well.
Spoon into crust and chill.

title: coconut crunch delight
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Press lightly in greased 13x9 pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes until golden brown, stirring every 10 minutes to form coarse crumbs.
Cool.
Divide crumbs in half.
Press half in same baking pan.
Beat pudding mixes & milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture over crust.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with strawberries (optional).

title: hardees' biscuits
directions: Stir up with a spoon.
Don't knead.
Pour out on floured board.
Roll out and cup cut.
Bake at 475° about 9 minutes.

title: fiesta bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in the bowl of a food processor, fitted with the steel blade. Process until smooth.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in a large bowl all ingredients, stirring until everything is thoroughly mixed.
Preheat oven to 250°.

title: grandmother tucker's chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, vinegar and meal; mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Use 2 table knives to cut eggs into sugar, etc. (do not stir).
Put into pie shell.
Place in oven that has been heated to 375°.
Immediately lower heat to 325° for 50 minutes, or until set or top is crusty.

title: beef tacos
directions: Brown beef in frying pan over high heat.
Add taco seasoning mix and water; stir.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
While beef is cooking, place taco shells in 350° preheated oven for 5 to 10 minutes.
Fill heated taco shells with 1 to 2 tablespoons meat. Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, taco sauce and sour cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli
for 5 minutes;
drain.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch
baking
dish.
Stir in cracker crumbs until covered with butter.
Reserve some for top.
Spread broccoli on top of crumbs. Spread
chicken
soup on top of broccoli.
Cover with slices of cheese and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add coconut; sprinkle over apples.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes, turning dish once.
Serve warm or cool topped with whipped cream.

title: iron skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Add all ingredients, mixing well.
Cook at 325° for 25 minutes in iron skillet.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Pour both bags of broccoli and cauliflower into a large casserole dish.
Add soups and 1 1/2 cans of water.
Add bacon, stuffing and half of each cheese.
Sprinkle top with Mrs. Dash and stir well. Spread remaining cheeses evenly over top and bake at 350° until done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard in large bowl.
Add macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans (reserving a few pecans for topping) until crumbly and press into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 300° about 20 minutes, until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: hot milk pound cake
directions: Beat in eggs, sugar and flour.
Bring to a boil the butter and milk, then add to mixture while
hot.
Next, add vanilla and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish potato rolls
directions: Melt margarine in milk.
In a large bowl beat eggs and add sugar, salt, milk, margarine and mashed potatoes.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to potato mixture.
Add flour and mix until stiff.
Cover and let rise thoroughly.
Punch down and cover again.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Roll out, cut and allow to rise for 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: rice supreme
directions: Boil chicken parts; remove from pot, reserving broth.
Cool and debone chicken.
Break chicken up into large pieces; set aside.
Cook rice in chicken broth and water, adding saffron. (Rice should be bright yellow in color.) Taste liquid and season with additional salt only if necessary.
(Rice should be thoroughly done.)
Place half the cooked rice in a casserole dish. Spread chicken over layer of rice; top chicken with remaining rice.
Spread mayonnaise on top of last layer of rice.
Cover with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is almost melted.
Yummy! Yummy!

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown beef and onion in a large skillet over medium heat. Drain.
Add vegetable soup or mixed vegetables.
Heat thoroughly. Serve over toasted buns.

title: chocolate-mint mini pies
directions: You will also need 18 cupcake papers.

title: tofu pie
directions: Mix Jell-O with water (1 3/4 cups hot water and 1/4 cup cold). Cool gelatin.
Mash tofu (drain liquid first before you mash it). Add tofu to gelatin, then add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill for about 3 hours.
Mixture will make 2 pies.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add boiling water a little at a time and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into lined cupcake tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: egg and ham casserole
directions: Cut bread into cubes. Add garlic. Place in 9 x 13 pan. Cover with ham and sprinkle cheese on top. Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over all. Refrigerate overnight. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Hard-boil eggs and potatoes.
Slice into bite size pieces. Mix with other ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap; let sit in the refrigerator until cold.

title: chicken bake
directions: Arrange tenders in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.

title: chicken breast - sauteed with new potatoes
directions: Saute chicken in large skillet in hot butter until both sides are brown.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook about 5 minutes.
In a small bowl combine flour, salt and pepper and slowly stir in bouillon cube which has been dissolved in the hot water.
Pour over browned chicken.
Cook slowly covered for about 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add potatoes and wine.
Heat potatoes thoroughly.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Combine all ingredients, except dressing.
Add dressing.
Toss gently.
Refrigerate, covered, for 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: italian zucchini meat pie
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, oats, 1/2 cup catsup, pepper, salt, onion and garlic powder.
Mix well and press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Fill partially baked meat shell with zucchini; combine Mozzarella, 1/2 cup catsup, olives (if desired), oregano and basil and pour over zucchini.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: yummers
directions: Mix all.
Form into balls.
Bake on 400° for 10 minutes.

title: angel food deluxe
directions: Melt chocolate in hot water until smooth and thick.
Add gelatine dissolved in cold water to the hot chocolate mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Beat egg yolks and add to the cooled chocolate mixture.
Beat egg whites, add sugar gradually and beat until thick and smooth.
Fold into chocolate mixture gently. Combine cake cubes into chocolate mixture, stirring gently and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or spring-form.
Keep in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: fried cheese sticks or cubes
directions: Coat cheese cubes with flour.
Dip in beaten egg, then add crumbs.
(If desired, prepare several hours ahead and refrigerate until needed).
Pour oil into fondue cooker to no more that 1/2 capacity or to depth of 2-inches.
Heat on range to 375°.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and transfer cooker to fondue burner.
Spear cheese with fondue fork.
Fry in hot oil for 20 to 30 seconds or until golden brown.

title: pickles
directions: Slice dill pickles; discard juice. Pour sugar and Tabasco over slices. Refrigerate for 1 week before eating. Stir every day.

title: vegetable beef soup(crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 12 to 24 hours (high for 4 to 6 hours).

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated and onion is cooked.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a saucepan heat the frozen broccoli and chopped onion for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and let bubble up with the broccoli and onion.
Add sliced cheese and milk; let it heat together, but do not boil.
Add seasoning.
Keep warm.
Serves 6.

title: luscious fruit fluff
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix Bisquick mix and 2 tablespoons sugar. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Press mixture in an ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake until light brown, about 15 minutes; cool.
Mix cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold cream and marshmallows into cheese mixture; spread over crust.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Cut into squares; top with fruit.
Makes 9 servings.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Let first 3 ingredients set overnight.
After setting overnight, drain and rinse, then add remaining ingredients. Bring to rolling boil, can and seal.

title: party slush punch
directions: Combine 2 quarts boiling water, sugar and citric acid, stirring until sugar and acid dissolves.
Combine pineapple juice (thawed), undiluted strawberry daiquiri mix and pink lemonade and 4 quarts of water.
Add to sugar mixture in large plastic container. Divide evenly into four 1-gallon size heavy-duty zip-top bags. Freeze.

title: raised buckwheat cakes
directions: Scald and cool milk.
Add yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in flour and salt.
Stir to a smooth batter.
Cover and let rise 12 hours or overnight.
Stir in molasses, soda mixture, egg and shortening.
Ladle on hot skillet, as with pancakes.
Serve with hot syrup or bacon gravy.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Combine.
Can also add mandarin oranges and maraschino cherries.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture forms coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and milk and add to flour mixture.
Stir until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead lightly, about 20 times. Roll dough 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with lightly floured 2-inch cutter, cutting straight down through the dough.

title: fried irish potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Heat pan with oil, then add potatoes. Cook on medium heat until brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add flavorings.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well at high speed.
Sift flour and salt.
Add slowly. Fold in coconut.
Bake 1 hour.
Frost with glaze.

title: chuck wagon pie
directions: Fry beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix. Spread meat in a 10-inch greased pie plate and top with drained chilies.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Arrange tomatoes over pie and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake an additional minute or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve with a dollop of sour cream.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Sift dry ingredients
together;
cut
in margarine with pastry blender.
Stir
in cheese.
Add Tabasco sauce to water and sprinkle, 1 tablespoon at a time, over ingredients, gently mixing and
pressing
with
fork
until dough holds together. Combine flour
and	paprika.
Sprinkle
on	long sheet of wax paper. Place
dough
on
paper,
roll into rectangle, turn to cover other
side
with paprika mixture.	Cut in half lengthwise, then cut crosswise in 3/4-inch strips.
Twist each strip 2 or 3 times; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press on ends. Bake at 450° about 10 minutes or until crisp.
Makes about 20.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle generously both sides of brisket with salts.
Pour liquid smoke over brisket.
Turn a couple of times.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain liquid smoke; add a little Worcestershire sauce. Seal well in heavy duty foil.
Cook at 275° for 1 hour per pound plus 1 hour.
The last hour, add barbecue sauce.
Open foil. Raise oven to 350°.
Let cool 30 minutes or so before slicing. Slice thin against grain.
If desired, add more barbecue sauce and reheat for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: blender chocolate mousse
directions: Beat egg whites in a small bowl with mixer until stiff, but not dry.
Place chocolate chips in container of blender.
Whirl to break up pieces.
Add boiling water or coffee; whirl until smooth. Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Whirl 1 minute until thoroughly blended.
Pour the chocolate mixture slowly over egg whites and fold in gently until no white shows.
Spoon into individual dishes and refrigerate for 1 hour or until firm and well chilled. Garnish with whipped cream, if you wish.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chocolate pound cake
directions: In mixing bowl combine liquid ingredients.
Add dry ingredients, then chips.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: smooth 'n creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding, powdered sugar and milk.
Beat at lowest speed for 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread.

title: baked pear pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 10 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss pears with raisins and cinnamon.
Spread in bottom of baking dish.
Spread bread slices generously with butter.
Cut each slice in half diagonally.
Arrange, overlapping in dish, buttered side up.
In pan, heat milk until bubbles form around edge of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and salt; stir to dissolve.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix wafer crumbs and butter thoroughly.
In 9-inch pie plate, press evenly on bottom and sides.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine marshmallows and milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows melt.
Cool thoroughly and add liqueurs.
Fold marshmallow mixture into whipped cream.
Add food coloring.
Pour into crumb lined pan.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: theresa shea's irish potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar.
Add butter, vanilla, salt and coconut.
Blend well.
Press into ungreased pan so that mixture is about 1-inch thick.
Chill until firm.
Cut into pieces, dipping pieces into melted semi-sweet chocolate.

title: stifado
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Dice onion.
Saute beef in oil. Add onion and saute together for three minutes.
Add tomatoes, vinegar, wine, bay leaves, salt, pepper, nutmeg, cinnamon, paprika, parsley and 2 cups warm water.
Cook on low heat for 2 1/2 hours. Peel onions and carve them like cross.
In a pan melt butter; add 1 cup water.
Add onions, garlic and salt.
Cook on low heat until water is gone.
Add onions to the beef and cook for the last 30 minutes of cooking.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all the ingredients except cabbage and carrots.
Finely shred cabbage and carrots.
Mix with dressing and let stand for 2 hours before serving.

title: veal marsala(makes 4 servings)
directions: Pound veal between wax paper.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Place on a piece of wax paper. Heat butter in skillet.
Dip veal in flour mixture as you are ready to cook them.
When butter stops foaming, add veal and brown quickly on both sides.
Transfer to warming platter.
Add onions to skillet, cook 4 minutes and add parsley, lemon juice and mushrooms.
Cook 1 minute, add wine and broth.
Boil until thick and turn heat to low and add scaloppine.
Serve at once.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Combine with 3 eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together .
Combine with sugar and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and the chocolate chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Get a baking pan, depending on how much you are going to make. Pour contents of can into the dish, juice included.
Put 1/2 box cake mix over the fruit.
Make sure it covers it evenly.
Put butter over the edges and middle.
Bake until top is brown and enjoy!

title: beef, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oil and add onion.
Cook until golden.
Add meat and cook until done. Add mushroom sauce. Arrange in casserole half of noodles, half of sauce and half of cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing at medium speed or mix until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and spread topping.

title: nachos
directions: Spread tortilla chips with small amount refried beans. Sprinkle on grated Cheddar cheese liberally.
Top with slices of peppers.
Bake on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: For 8 halves, bring 4 eggs to a boil starting with cold water. Cover, remove from heat.
Let stand 12 minutes; drain and peel. Cut in half lengthwise.
Mix together mayonnaise, dry mustard, salt, pepper and egg yolks.
Spread mixture on each half egg whites.

title: cheese rice krispie
directions: Mix cheese and margarine.
Add flour and mix well.
Add crispy cereal and mix well.
Shape into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten each ball with fork and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: vegetable stuffed flounder
directions: Cut zucchini and red pepper into
thin strips.
Combine vegetables in bowl with Stove Top, hot water, broth, 2 tablespoons butter and tarragon.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon and press stuffing onto half of each fillet.
Fold fillet over stuffing. Mix remaining butter and paprika; brush on fillets.
Place stuffed fillets in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish is easily flaked with a fork.

title: country ham casserole
directions: Heat cheese, milk and salad dressing over low heat; stir until sauce is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until hot. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: herb dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Great with vegetables.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix and shape into loaf.
Wrap in wax paper; chill overnight.

title: york peppermint brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl with spoon, stir together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Reserve 2 cups of batter and set aside.
Spread remaining batter in prepared pan.
Arrange patties in single layer over batter about 1/2 inch apart.
Spread reserved batter over patties.
Bake 50 minutes or until brownies pull away from pan.
Enjoy!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and let cool.
Dice bell pepper and onion. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, beaten eggs and lemon.
Add dry mixture with raisins and pecans.
Bake 2 1/2 hours in 10-inch tube pan (greased and floured) at 275°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; put into casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers with melted butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: sea legs casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter. Add cooking sherry.
Mix flour with water to make paste.
Add to chicken bouillon.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into mushrooms and cook over medium heat to thicken. Do not boil, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sea legs and sour cream.
Heat to warm.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine vegetables, cheese and bacon in large bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Add dressing shortly before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Shred boiled chicken into medium sized pieces.
Mix with sour cream and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and melt enough butter to saturate crackers, then pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: freezer corn
directions: Cook 2 minutes. Cool.
Put in freezer bags.

title: philly-style cheese steaks
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium-high heat cook steaks for 2 minutes or until desired doneness, turning once.
In same skillet, add soup mix blended with water.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Return steaks to skillet and cook 1 minute or until heated through.
To serve, place steak on rolls.
Top with sauce and cheese.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef with green peppers and onions.
Drain, then add Pizza Quick sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Put mixture in baking dish.
On top of this, add mushrooms, pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese (whatever you like on your pizza).
Mix flour, milk, oil and beaten eggs.
Pour batter on top of mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, crumbs, egg, onion, pepper and salt.
Shape into 6 patties.
Brown patties in a small amount of shortening in skillet.
Pour fat off.
Stir in remaining soup and water.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: biscuits
directions: Put it in the sifter and sift it.
Then add your shortening until it starts coming together.
Grease your pans.
Cut out your biscuits with a biscuit cutter.
Put in the oven at 400°.

title: grilled mushrooms
directions: Thread mushrooms onto skewers.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush over mushrooms.
Grill over hot coals 10 to 15 minutes, basting and turning every 5 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly.
Add any pie filling on top.
Must be canned filling, not fresh.

title: hamburger roll
directions: Mix Bisquick and enough water to make a soft dough.
Roll into a rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Mix hamburger, soup and onion.
Spread thin onto Bisquick and roll up.
Cut into 1 1/4-inch slices and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve topped with hot mushroom soup poured over (don't thin the soup too much).

title: golden meatball casserole
directions: Form meatballs from ground meat, egg and crackers; brown in skillet coated with Pam.
When brown, remove meatballs from skillet; drain and rinse.
Return meatballs to skillet.
Add rice, carrots and 2 cups of water.
Cover and cook on medium-high heat until carrots are done (approximately 20 to 30 minutes).
You may need to add water.
After water is absorbed and carrots are done, cover with cheese slices, then cover with lid until cheese melts.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Put
cucumbers	and
onion in bowl.
Sprinkle salt over them and let stand 3 hours.
Rinse in cold water.
Add sugar, vinegar and seed.
Put this over cucumbers and onions.
Put in refrigerator
overnight.
Put
in
containers
and in freezer. Thaw to eat.

title: lite stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Stir-fry chicken in oil until brown.
Add water chestnuts, green pepper strips and broccoli; let stir-fry with chicken.
Mix broth and dry ingredients together.
Add to pan and bring to boil. Serve over rice.

title: tomatoes rougaille
directions: Combine peppers and tomatoes; blend water, Tabasco sauce and salt.
Stir into vegetables.
May be served with Curry Chicken.
