title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Cool 15 minutes and poke holes in cake.

title: easy orange pudding
directions: You will need a 2 or 3-quart shallow baking dish and 1 larger baking dish (large enough to hold the 2-quart baking dish).

title: lou ellen's strawberry 3-layer
directions: Crust:
Combine flour, butter and pecans.
Pat evenly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: vegetarian gravy
directions: Combine butter and flour in saucepan on medium heat.
With wire whisk slowly add water.
Bring to a boil until thickened.
Add onion, garlic, tamari and molasses for color.

title: granny young's pork chops
directions: Place apples in 9 x 13-inch pan; place onion on top of apples. Place pork chops on top.
Pour bottled or homemade barbecue sauce over all.
Bake at 400° until pork chops are done.

title: none such bread
directions: Add mincemeat to prepared mix.
Then prepare mix according to directions on package.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Turn out onto cooling rack.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Melt the chocolate in the coffee.
Dissolve gelatine in water and add to coffee and chocolate mixture.
Stir well.
Add to egg and sugar mixture, beat well and cool.
When cool, but not set, beat egg whites and when partly beaten, add sugar (1/2 cup) and beat until stiff.
Add to cooled chocolate mixture.
Stir or beat on slow until mixture is thoroughly mixed.
Store in refrigerator until served with whipped cream.
Fills one pie.

title: no name spread
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons cheese to top with.
Place into small baking dish.
Top with 2 tablespoons cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut up chicken breast and boil for 30 minutes.
Mix first 3 ingredients and place in baking dish.
Crumble crackers on top and sprinkle on poppy seeds.
Cut up butter and layer the top.
Cook 350° until brown.

title: fried cheese
directions: Cut cheese in strips.
Beat egg.
Dip cheese in egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil.

title: beef ribs in a bag
directions: Sprinkle ribs with unseasoned tenderizer and place in bag. Mix barbecue sauce and wine.
Pour over ribs.
Tie bag.
Vent bag and cook at 350° for 2 hours.

title: oyster soup
directions: Bring oysters to boil in 1 cup water.
Add margarine, mix and then add milk and salt to taste.
Stir and heat to boiling point. Serve with crackers.

title: no-knead whole wheat bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in honey; add butter, salt and whole wheat flour.
Beat on low speed until well blended.
Stir in all-purpose flour.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Grease and flour a 17 x 11 x 3/4-inch cookie sheet.

title: potato cheese pie
directions: Mix raw hamburger, onion, cereal and eggs.
Press into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Peel and boil potatoes, mash while still hot and stir in cheese.
Pour potato and cheese mixture into meat shell.
Top with additional cheese and parsley. Bake until warm again and cheese on top has melted.

title: mr. b's chili
directions: Brown the meat in the oil (in batches) along with the other first 3 ingredients. Mix the remaining (last 7 ingredients on list) together in bowl and allow to stand 2 to 3 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain can of pineapple. Set juice aside. Melt butter and mix with sugar. Stir in pineapple with sugar and butter. Mix. Sprinkle flour in as you stir in these ingredients. Crush Ritz crackers. Stir in crackers and cup of shredded cheese to the mixture. Add 1 tablespoon of pineapple juice to mixture. Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Can be served warm or cooled.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add 1 cup flour with soda in it.
Next, add buttermilk, then other cup of flour.
Add cocoa mixture and then 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain off grease.
Add onion and flour; cook onion with meat until tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients and add as much water as needed.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: pork chops and potato
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt.
Brown slowly on both sides. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the potatoes in the baking pan and pour over the potatoes the mixture of soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Put chops on top of the potatoes in the baking pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4.

title: coconut creme pie
directions: Stir sugar and flour together.
Add milk, beaten egg yolks and margarine.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Stir well.
Pour into browned pie shells.
Top with beaten egg whites and brown.

title: "softball quickie"
directions: Wrap hot dogs with one slice of bacon.
Broil until bacon cooks.
Great served with macaroni and cheese as an easy to fix lunch.

title: pizzelles(italian cookies)
directions: Beat eggs until very frothy and add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add cooled, melted shortening and margarine (or butter). Gradually add flour, baking powder and salt.
Let set a few minutes before cooking.

title: deluxe chicken breast
directions: Place chicken breast between wax paper. Flatten slightly with your hands. Whisk egg yolks with water. Combine flour, salt, pepper, paprika, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Dip chicken in egg yolks. Roll in flour crumb mixture. Brown chicken in butter on both sides. Place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes. Prepare cheese sauce while chicken is cooking. After chicken is cooked, cover with cheese sauce; garnish with bell pepper rings, if desired.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together milk and egg; add fat.
Add mixture to cornmeal mixture.
Stir to mix. Grease baking pan.
Fill half full.
Bake in oven preheated 425° for about 25 minutes or until browned.

title: layered cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in 1 cup cold water.
Pour 1
1/2 cups raspberry gelatin into 6-cup mold. Chill until
slightly firm.
Reserve remaining gelatin. Do not chill.
Beat 1/2
cup
sugar
and
cream
cheese
until creamy. Gradually add
evaporated
milk
and vanilla.
Soften unflavored gelatin in remaining
cup
cold water in small saucepan. Heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Blend into cheese mixture. Carefully spoon mixture
over raspberry gel in mold. Chill until slightly firm.
Add
remaining
cup sugar and cranberries to reserved
raspberry gelatin.
Stir until blended.
Carefully pour mixture
over
cheese
layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.

title: chicken livers supreme
directions: Cook livers in 2 cups of the broth.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Combine rice, livers and mushrooms in a casserole.
Use the other cup of broth to make it slightly soupy.
It might take a little more broth.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: frozen mint pie
directions: In large bowl, mix condensed milk, extract and food coloring. Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into crust and cover.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Makes 1 pie.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain grease.
Add other ingredients. Mix together.
Put in skillet and cook on low heat for 20 minutes or until done.
Eat on buns.

title: apricot or orange fruit gelatin
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water.
Allow to thicken.
Drain pineapple; add to gelatin and congeal until firm in 7 x 11-inch pan.

title: low calorie parmesan fillets
directions: Preheat broiler.
In cup or small bowl, combine oil and lemon juice.
On nonstick baking sheet, arrange fillets in a single layer and, using pastry brush, brush both sides of each fillet with 1/4 of the oil mixture.
Sprinkle top of each fillet with half of the cheese.
Broil until golden brown and fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, 3 to 4 minutes.
Makes 2 servings, 166 calories.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
In another mixing bowl, combine beaten egg, milk and cooking oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Stir nuts and cherries into batter.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: southern style collard greens
directions: Wipe each half with damp dishcloth.
Put leaves in kitchen sink; wash each leaf separately and put in a large dishpan; wipe each leaf and put with several leaves and roll them in a ball to cut evenly in small 1/2-inch strips.
With a sharp knife (the size you use for cole slaw); remove stalks and large stems from leaves before cutting.
Slice salt pork into small slices for frying.
If using ham hocks precook before preparing the greens.
Pour the cooked salt pork and fat into a large cooking pot; add the cut greens, the salt and water.
Cover and cook until tender over medium heat.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hearts of romaine salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients; toss.
Divide on 8 serving plates.
Drizzle with Vinaigrette Dressing to which the capers have been added.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix together; put in casserole dish.

title: crawfish soup
directions: If bream
are
small
cook
them whole, but if they are large split
them
down the center.
Salt both sides and place in refrigerator for about 2 hours and remove and wipe off with paper towel.
Cook
in
hot
oil	in frying pan until brown on both sides.
(Peanut oil is preferred but any good cooking oil will do.)

title: tropical delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender and add ice. Sprinkle with coconut if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and powder, then put aside.
Mix the bananas, oil, honey or syrup, vanilla and eggs together, then add the flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cool in pan, then remove.
Good as a snack!

title: no seal pickles
directions: Cut up cucumbers.
Cover in salt water, that will float an egg, for 8 days.
Drain.
Wash in clear water; soak overnight in alum water.
Use 3 tablespoons of alum to 1 gallon of water.
Wash and drain.
Cover cucumbers in vinegar and soak for 6 hours.
Drain off vinegar.
Alternate layer of pickles, layer of sugar and 2 tablespoons mixed spice.

title: mom's butter balls
directions: Place sugar and softened butter into large bowl; cream together.
Add vanilla and nuts until creamy.
Then add flour until it forms a dough.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli into tiny flowerets, peel stems and dice. Slice 1 onion very thin. Dice up 4 pieces of bacon and fry, drain well.
Use enough mayonnaise to moisten mixture.
Salt lightly if desired.

title: richest ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat
butter,
eggs,
sugar and vanilla until light and creamy.
Sift
flour,
salt
and baking soda together.
Add to creamed
mixture and blend thoroughly.
Dough will be slightly crumbly.
Drop
by
large
spoonfuls or form a small ice cream scoop onto
a
greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are light.
Do not overbake.

title: best peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter into a deep baking dish.
Pour batter of 1 cup sugar, flour and milk into center, but do not stir.
Pour 2 cups fruit or berries mixed with 3/4 cup sugar into the middle of the batter, but do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add sifted confectioners sugar until consistency of pie dough.
Roll out between wax paper.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll, cut and chill.

title: beef stew(tomato gravy)
directions: Brown meat in oil, in pan you are going to cook stew in. Drain grease and add tomato sauce (plus 1 & 1/2 cans water), carrots, onion, & potatoes that have been cut into cubes. Salt & pepper. Cook with lid at medium temp. until tender.

title: bread (wheat)
directions: Set your oven to 350°.
Mix warm water and yeast; let stand while measuring sugar, molasses, oil, wheat flour and white flour. Add salt last.
Pour water and yeast mix on flour; mix and knead until it is right.
Let raise.
Knead down and let raise a second time, then put in loaves and let rise until double in size, then bake 40 minutes or more.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.

title: cordelia knott's recipe - buttermilk biscuits
directions: Into a mixing bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and blend well.
Add baking soda to buttermilk, then pour into flour mixture.
Blend thoroughly.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour soups into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add 3 cans of water.
Pour instant rice into can.
Fill 3 times.
Mix to moisten.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake 90 minutes at 350°.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Put 2 cans peaches with juice in oblong pan (13 x 9-inches). Pour 1/2 box dry cake mix over peaches.
Pour milk over mix and peaches.
Stir lightly, mixing ingredients.
Pour rest of cake mix over peach mixture, then pour cup of butter on top of dry mix. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Butter 4 individual casseroles.
Add a few grains of nutmeg to the white sauce, then add the broccoli and mix carefully so as not to break the vegetable.
Divide the creamed broccoli evenly between the 4 casseroles.
Press 2 deviled egg halves in the top of each, pushing the eggs well down so that only the golden yolks show.
Heat at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Eggs are delicious with broccoli.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges (rind too); stir in sugar.
Make jello using hot water; pour over cranberry and orange mixture.
Add celery and pecans.
Congeal.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together; salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.

title: black linguine with calamari and scallops in a garlic butter sauce
directions: Saute in olive oil, garlic, calamari, scallops and basil. Deglaze with white wine; add salt and pepper.
Reduce 1/2 of liquid.
Add tomatoes; add butter at the end.
Warm pasta.
Serve on top of black linguine and garnish with fresh basil.

title: freezer sweet pickles
directions: Mix thoroughly first 3 ingredients.
Let stand 2 1/2 hours. Drain well; mix together sugar and vinegar and add to cucumbers. Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Place in freezer container and freeze immediately.

title: creamy almond chicken
directions: Saute almonds in butter; set aside.
Place chicken between wax paper and beat to 1/4 inch pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Melt remaining 3 tablespoons butter; add chicken.
Cook 1 minute on each side on medium-high.
Reduce to medium.
Add 1/2 cup almonds, cream and next 3 ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix everything together except 3/4 cup chow mein noodles.
Pour into greased casserole and top with remaining noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Combine evaporated milk, marshmallows and orange juice in a small bowl; let stand for 30 minutes.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, coconut, nuts (raisins) and ready to use fruits and peels.
Stir in marshmallow mix with a spoon until all crumbs are moistened. Press firmly into wax-lined 9-inch loaf pan.
Cover tightly. Store at least 2 days in refrigerator before serving.
Slice thin to serve.
Cake will keep for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: chicken acapulco with peanuts
directions: Saute onion in margarine in a small saucepan until tender.
In a large bowl, mix the sauteed onion with the next 8 ingredients, mixing well.
Reserve 1 can of soup.
Spoon 2/3 cup of chicken mixture in center of each tortilla.
Roll up; place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine the shredded cheese and 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Spread over the tortillas.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix well and pour in a baked or graham cracker crust pie shell.
Top with whipped meringue.
Brown in oven.
Chill well in icebox or fridge.
Very refreshing in summer.

title: barbecued wieners
directions: Prick wieners with fork and place in greased casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over wieners.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup of salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Stir and refrigerate until serving time.

title: strawberry swirl salad squares
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir to thaw strawberries, using a large fork to break up frozen berries.
Stir in 1/2 cup water.
Turn mixture into an ungreased 8-inch square baking dish.
Refrigerate until partially set.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese and milk with electric mixer on medium speed until fluffy.
Beat in mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of gelatin. Cut through cheese mixture with a knife to create a marbled effect. Refrigerate until set.
Arrange lettuce leaves on salad plates. Cut salad into squares and serve on lettuce-lined plates.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Slice enough potatoes into greased 6-quart casserole to make a good layer.
Place ground beef on top and season with salt and pepper.
Layer onion on top and then another layer of sliced potatoes.
Pour soup over all that has been mixed with a 1/2 can of water.
Cover and bake at 350° until potatoes are tender. Uncover last few minutes to brown top.

title: russian easter kulich
directions: Sprinkle yeast onto warm water.
Dissolve.
In large bowl, combine milk, sugar, margarine, vanilla, cardamon and salt.
Add yeast, then eggs, stirring until well blended.
Add glazed fruit, then gradually beat in flour.
Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl, cover with towel and let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 2 hours. Punch down dough.
Divide into 2 or 4 sections; place each into a well-greased can.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size again.

title: peachy cherry wine soup(a refreshing starter for a summer meal.)
directions: Cook all ingredients until boiling, except wine, cornstarch and sour cream.
Mix cornstarch into wine and stir into boiling soup until thickened.
Cool in refrigerator several hours.

title: 3 minute microwave fudges
directions: Put chips and milk in microwave bowl; microwave 3 minutes, stir; continue until smooth.
May need to microwave longer.
May add nuts, if desired.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch or oblong cake pan, lightly buttered.
Chill until set.
Empty out and cut into pieces.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients beginning and ending with lettuce.
I usually put 2 layers of all vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise, black pepper and Red Hot to taste.
Should be spicy.
Spread over top of vegetables.
Cover completely with no lettuce showing.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 6 hours or more before serving.
This takes a while to make and I find it's really easy to make several at one time, keep one and take the others as treats for friends.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix soup, cheese, tomatoes, onion and bell pepper in saucepan until cheese is melted.
Spread in casserole dish a layer of broken chips and then a layer of chicken.
Top with layer of sauce mixture.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Top with layer of finely crushed chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 300° or until hot all the way through.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Make pudding according to directions, using 3 cups milk.
When cake is cooled, cut into small pieces and pour Kahlua over it.
Refrigerate and allow cake and pudding to set overnight.
To serve, layer in order the cake, pudding, cream, crushed candy bars and nuts in a glass bowl, making as many layers as desired.
I usually make three layers.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, eggs, oil, dry instant pudding, water and poppy seed.
Mix well with electric mixer, about 4 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick tests clean in center. Cool.

title: hurry up cake
directions: In bowl add first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
In another bowl, add sugar, shortening, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: dr. pepper cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cinnamon and dash of salt.
Bring to a boil in pan oleo, oil, cocoa and Dr. Pepper.
Mix with sifted items.
Add 2 beaten eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and soda.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease and flour three (9-inch) round layer pans.
Pour boiling water over cocoa; stir to dissolve.
Add buttermilk.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt onto wax paper.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat dry ingredients into butter alternating with cocoa mixture.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Divide batter evenly in pans.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes and then turn out on racks.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Dissolve gelatine in a small amount of hot water.
Mix ingredients.
Place in prepared mold(s).
Refrigerate to chill. Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows with butter.
Butter wooden spoon and mix popcorn, nuts and jelly beans.
Let mixture sit for 2 minutes, then fill a buttered angel food cake pan.
Cool completely before removing.

title: seafoam cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs, one at a	time,
and
beat well.	Add syrup.
Alternately add milk and sifted
dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake in layers in a 375° oven 25 minutes.
Frost with Seafoam Icing.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Layer refried beans in platter evenly.
Mix taco seasoning mix with sour cream and spread over beans.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve with large corn chips.
Yields about 6 cups.

title: frugal gourmet's coleslaw
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large bowl.
Sprinkle vegetables with 1/4 cup sugar; stir occasionally.
In a stainless steel pan, heat remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over vegetables. Let marinate for several hours.
This salad keeps for about a week in the refrigerator.

title: quick cranberry bread
directions: Sift the flour with soda, baking powder and salt.
In mixing bowl, by hand or mixer, beat the eggs and sugar until well blended. Stir in melted butter and milk mixed with rose water.
Stir in the flour, just until moistened, and then fold in cranberries and nuts (do not overwork dough).
Butter a loaf pan, 10 inches long and 4 to 5 inches wide and spread the dough in pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until center of bread springs back when lightly touched.
Let stand in pan for a few minutes before turning out on rack to cool.
When cooled, wrap in plastic or foil and let sit overnight or at least a day before cutting. Store in the refrigerator.

title: 15 minute no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Stir quickly.
Drop by spoons on waxed paper.

title: chicken italian style
directions: In a large baking dish, place chicken, egg noodles and bell pepper.
Sprinkle dry ingredients over chicken.
Mix barbecue sauce and water; pour over the top.
Cover; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: flounder in lemon sauce
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat, heat first five ingredients, stirring occasionally, until butter or oleo is melted and hot.
If flounder fillets are large, cut into serving-size pieces.

Add flounder to butter mixture in skillet; cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes, until flounder flakes easily when tested with a fork, basting flounder occasionally with butter mixture in skillet. Arrange flounder with its sauce in warm, deep platter.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serves 4.

title: scripture cake
directions: Whip Judges, Jeremiah and 1 Samuel until light.
Beat the 6 Jeremiah yolks and add to first ingredients.
Then, add 1 Kings, Amos, Chronicles and Leviticus, alternately with Judges.
Fold in Nahum, Numbers and 1 Samuel 30:12.
Add the Jeremiah whites, beaten stiff.
Bake 2 hours at 300° in greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together and beat 2 minutes until smooth. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine lemon juice and milk.
Add other ingredients and fold in.
This can be served as is or put in loaf pan and frozen. Slice and serve.
May be used as a salad or a dessert.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of hot water.
While jello is cooling, beat chilled milk until stiff.
In another bowl, beat cream cheese mixture into milk.
Beat until mixed; add jello.

title: corn-stuffed zucchini
directions: Boil zucchini until tender, 8 minutes.
Cut in half lengthwise and remove center with teaspoon.
Turn half over to drain.
Mix eggs, corn, scallions, oregano, salt and diced squash center.
Put zucchini in shallow pan; sprinkle with salt and fill centers with corn mixture.
Bake until set, then sprinkle with cheese and bake until melted.

title: blueberry treat
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Allow to cool.

title: wheat bread
directions: Mix gluten flour, salt and yeast in large bowl.
Mix water, honey, margarine and cottage cheese in saucepan.
Heat to 125°. Margarine may not melt.
Add warm mixture to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moist.
Add 4 eggs and beat for 3 minutes. Stir in oatmeal, nuts and 6 cups flour.
Turn onto cupboard and knead 10 minutes adding extra flour if needed.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours. Divide into 4 loaves.
Rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick lemonade punch
directions: Pour lemonade drink over sherbet.
Let stand for a short time. Stir and serve.

title: len's meat loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Divide into 2 or 3 smaller loaves. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Drain grease off.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in microwave as directed on package.
Melt margarine. Stir in crackers and put aside.
Grease a 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put in vegetables.
Add cheese on top and sprinkle cracker mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Put remaining in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and the other egg until light and smooth. Smooth over baked layer and sprinkle reserved cup of mixture.
Bake an additional 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream powdered sugar and cheese together.
Add peanut butter. Beat with mixer.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour in baked or graham cracker pie shell.
Chill.

title: one dish meal
directions: Fry hamburger until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir gently.
Cover.
Cook slowly over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening with sugar. Add eggs, milk and flour. Mix well. Add cream bananas. Put into a loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: filling for cake
directions: Put raisins, dates, nuts and coconut through food chopper. Put into saucepan.
Add other ingredients and cook over very low heat until thick enough to spread.

title: pickled cow tongue
directions: Put tongue in large kettle.
Cover with water and 2 teaspoons of salt.
Cook until done, approximately 6 hours.
Remove from water.
Peel tongue and slice.
Combine all ingredients, except tongue.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over tongue; let stand until cool.
Refrigerate for 2 days.

title: baked creamed cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage very fine and cook 9 minutes in boiling water. Drain cabbage well and place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt margarine in saucepan and stir in flour and vegie-sal until smooth.
Add soy milk gradually; continue stirring until thickened.
Pour sauce over cabbage and sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: In a blender, process first 7 ingredients until smooth. Transfer to a small bowl; stir in cheese.
Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups dressing.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut up into small squares or 1/4 biscuits.
Shake well white sugar and cinnamon.
Mix brown sugar and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: In one saucepan, combine chocolate pudding and 2 1/2 cups milk. In another saucepan, combine vanilla pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk. Cook both until they boil and thicken over medium heat. Stir peanut butter into vanilla pudding. Drop warm pudding into crust, alternating chocolate and peanut butter; swirl together. Chill completely. Serve with dollops of whipped cream.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in dry covered jar.
Use 3 teaspoons per cup.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: In a heavy pan, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Cook until melted.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine dry cake mix, melted butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
By hand, stir until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread caramel mixture over baked dough.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramel layer.
Crumble reserved dough over caramel mix layer.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool slightly, then refrigerate about 1 hour before cutting.

title: wimpies
directions: Mix chili powder with hamburg and brown meat.
Add seasonings, ketchup, mustard and remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1/2 hour. Vegetables should be on the hard side.

title: mock's cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl; add buttermilk and egg.
Mix. Heat iron skillet or pie pan with shortening or bacon grease. Pour heated grease into mixture and mix well.
Pour entire mixture into hot skillet or pan.
Bake at 400° until done (20 to 25 minutes).

title: rumaki
directions: Combine soy sauce and sugar; marinate chestnuts in mixture at least 30 minutes.
Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap each chestnut and secure with a toothpick.
Bake about 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp at 400°.
Turn if necessary.
This can be done ahead.
To rewarm, put in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute eggplant separately.
Saute the remaining ingredients together; add in order given.
Add salt, pepper, basil, coriander and clove of garlic.
Let cook on stove about 45 minutes.

title: tropical cream punch
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk and juices in punch bowl; mix well. Add club soda and stir. Refrigerate. Serve over ice.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini and onions and soak overnight in salted water. Drain, rinse, combine in pan with remainder of ingredients, and cook for five (5) minutes.
Put into clean jars and seal.

title: pork chop-n-potato bake
directions: Brown chops in skillet with oil.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can fried onions.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix first three and put into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and pats of butter.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.

title: zeppole
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remainder of ingredients and beat gently until combined batter becomes sticky.
Drop by half teaspoon (push off batter with another spoon) into deep corn oil; heat to 375°, frying a few at a time, until Zeppole are golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain on brown paper and roll in confectioners sugar.
Serve at once.
Makes 36.

title: apple brickle dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use with sliced apples.
Soak apple slices in pineapple juice to prevent them from turning dark.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, corn syrup, sugar, flour and vanilla extract in mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until center is firm to the touch.

title: mama's nut cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter in electric mixer.
Add eggs, beating after each egg.
Beat in flour, adding milk only if needed.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nuts by hand.
Put in floured tube pan and cook in oven at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: carrot pasta fettucini with shrimp newburg sauce
directions: In a food processor, add 2 cups flour, carrots, egg and 1 tablespoon oil.
Pulse.
Add water and flour as needed to form a ball.
Remove dough to a well-floured surface.
Roll flat.
Either pass it through a pasta cutter or take a knife and cut pasta into long thin strips about 8 inches long by 1/2-inch wide.
Let rest. Bring 2 quarts water, salted, to a boil.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a bowl, drain pineapple, reserving juices.
In a saucepan, mix together reserved juice, 1/2 cup water and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring thoroughly. Break up cranberry sauce with fork and stir into gelatin mixture. Refrigerate until mixture begins to set.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: simple m&m cookies
directions: Stir together and drop on baking sheet. Bake until set.

title: bulldog brittle
directions: Break graham crackers into fourths.
Place in foil-lined 10 x 15-inch baking pan, leaving space between crackers.
Sprinkle pecans over top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bring chicken, water and 1 teaspoon salt to a boil in Dutch oven; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove chicken, reserving broth.
Skin, bone and chop chicken; set aside.
Skim fat from broth, reserving 2 cups broth.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork in shortening. Add water; cover and simmer 1 hour. Combine cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce; cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Pour sauce over hot pork; let stand 10 minutes. Add green peppers, onion and pineapple chunks. Cook 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings. Serve with rice.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Place in crock-pot:
1 pound hamburger, 1 large can tomatoes, 1 package frozen mixed vegetables, salt and pepper to taste.
Secret ingredient is oregano (start with 1/4 teaspoon and increase to taste).
Slow cook overnight.
Serve with homemade corn or light bread.
Crackers, if no bread.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in refrigerator overnight. Next morning, bake a yellow cake mix in 2 pans.
Cool and split in 4 layers.
Take coconut mixture and spread between layers, on top and on sides of cake.
Cover and refrigerate for 5 days before serving.

title: hungry man's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Add next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Cook for 10 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients except grated cheese in bowl, mixing well.
Layer noodle mixture and ground beef mixture alternately in greased casserole until all ingredients are used. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: danish puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour until size of small peas.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over flour mixture.
Mix.
Make a ball of the mixture and divide into halves. Pat each half into rectangle, 12 x 3-inch, on ungreased cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart.

title: crunchy peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter.
Remove from heat and mix in large bowl, melted butter, milk, sugar and peanut butter.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, beaten eggs and oil.
Blend together with flour that has been sifted together with dry ingredients. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°, then 20 minutes at 350° in a large, greased tube pan.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together and pour over cabbage, pepper, onion and spices.
Stir well and store in refrigerator about 12 to 24 hours before using.
Keeps well for several days.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Mix all together.
Boil vinegar and oil one minute.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour the hot vinegar and oil over the cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.
Drain and serve.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add nuts.
Fold in large Cool Whip.
Add ReaLemon juice.
Mix and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill several hours.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Boil rhubarb and sugar 10 minutes (rolling boil).
Set off fire.
Add red raspberry jello.
Put in glasses.

title: butternut cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and Crisco. Add milk and flavoring. Gradually beat in flour.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans until golden brown, 18 to 20 minutes.

title: country style relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients, using blade of food grinder. Drain.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to full boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Place in clean, hot jars and seal. Makes about 9 pints.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Break lettuce into small pieces.
Place in bottom of long casserole dish.
Spread onion over lettuce.
Spread celery over lettuce.
Pour drained green peas over celery.
Use a spatula to spread mayonnaise over peas.
Sprinkle cheese, then bacon bits over mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain off fat. In 9 x 13 pan, put 1/2 bag of Tostitos (crushed) in bottom. Then put 1/4 pound of Velveeta (cubed) over chips. In separate bowl, mix together soups and enchilada sauce. Pour meat mixture over cheese and chips. Then pour soup mixture over meat. Cube another 1/4 pound of Velveeta on top and add the rest of the crushed chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into a lightly greased, small casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with assorted crackers (warm).

title: baked fruit
directions: Drain all fruit.
Place in ovenproof casserole.
Mix until crumbly the cornstarch, sugar, butter and curry powder.
Place over fruit.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: super cheesy beans
directions: Heat oil in a large pan.
Add onion and cook until clear.
Add beans and mash using a little water or bean liquid if necessary. Sprinkle cheese over beans.
Stir to melt cheese and serve.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix pineapple, lemon, cranberry juice and sugar.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Can be put in freezer or use immediately.

title: chilli pizza
directions: Mix the dough as directed.
Add your sauce, then 1/2 of the can of chilli, mushrooms, olives and cheese.
Put into a preheated oven at 425° for 30 or 35 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin.
Arrange in alternate layers with onion in a 1 1/2-quart casserole, salting each layer slightly.
Melt butter in a saucepan; add flour and blend.
Add milk and cook and stir until smooth and thickened.
Add salt and blend.

Pour over potatoes; cover casserole and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes; then uncover and continue to bake for 25 or 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender and lightly browned on top.

title: pat's spice cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan that has been sprayed with pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool; top with Cool Whip.

title: green salad
directions: Mix the first three ingredients in a large bowl.
In another bowl mix the next six ingredients.
Pour the liquid ingredients over the salad right before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine apples, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and dump into apple mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 55 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Place ingredients in bowl; beat.
Use for carrots, celery, green peppers, tomatoes, broccoli, cauliflower, etc.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mom's beef barbecue
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in oil; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat over low flame.
Serve on buns.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Blend in pumpkin. Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add alternately with water, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts or raisins.
Pour into 3 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: fudge clusters
directions: In a saucepan, mix together sugar, milk and margarine. After it comes to a boil, continue cooking 7 more minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop mixture by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: finger jello
directions: *You can also use apple juice concentrate.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Stir together egg and water; then add the first 4 ingredients. Shape into balls (4 to 6, depending upon size of pie pan).
Chill in refrigerator for 15 or more minutes.
Roll out on floured wax paper.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Use for making your favorite baked pie.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven until the celery is cooked.

title: aunt lucille's drop cookies
directions: Blend softened butter, eggs and sugar.
Combine soda and flour into mixture.
Add cold coffee, nutmeats, vanilla and spices. Stir until creamy.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoons or tablespoons (your choice).
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: yum yum pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light. Add beaten egg yolks, vinegar and spices. Beat good. Add beaten egg whites. Mix well, add chopped raisins, mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 350 degree oven until knife comes out clean.

title: roll out cookies
directions: This firm vanilla sugar cookie recipe easily releases from cutters.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix eggs and oil.
Add flavoring and beat well.
Add lemon Jell-O (cooled).
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pan for 45 minutes.

title: pasta with shrimp and wine
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen.
In saucepan cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter and olive oil until tender, but not brown. Stir in wine, bouillon granules, basil, garlic (if used), salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, for 12 to 15 minutes or until liquid is reduced by 2/3.

title: state fair lemonade
directions: Slice lemon in half.
Squeeze juice from lemon into jar with lid.
Drop in lemon halves.
Add water and sugar.
Cover jar and shake vigorously.
Remove lemon halves and serve lemonade over ice.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and boil 3 minutes. Remove from the heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Beat together and spoon on wax paper.

title: oven fried fish fillets
directions: Cut the fillets into serving pieces.
Dip the fillets in milk and roll in the cracker crumbs.
Place on a shallow, well-greased baking pan.
Sprinkle each piece with melted margarine.
Bake in a 500° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until the fish flakes.
A nice ending is a few minutes before fish is done, place a slice of Swiss cheese on each piece of fish.

title: doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or just until set.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together corn meal, flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Add chopped onion.
Combine egg with buttermilk, add dry ingredients and stir just enough to blend.
Drop by spoonfuls into fat where fish is cooking.
Put on absorbent paper to drain. Makes 36 to 48 small hush puppies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese together.
Mix together butter, cream cheese, corn (drained) and chilies.
Put in a casserole dish and heat until bubbly.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and chill. When jello thickens, add sour cream.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.

title: beef and veggie macaroni
directions: Cook 1 cup macaroni and drain.
Brown ground beef, add remaining ingredients, salt and pepper and macaroni.
Put in greased casserole, bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with Durkee onions the last 10 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Drop in greased muffin tins and bake at 400°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: possum pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and sugar gradually.
Beat until peaks.
Fold in nuts and crackers, etc. Lightly grease pie pan.
Pour in mixture of egg whites, crackers and nuts.
Put in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
After cooled, add whipped topping and sprinkle coconut on top.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot.
Cook on low heat several hours until liquid absorbs and meat falls apart.

title: pink popcorn balls
directions: Place popped corn in large buttered bowl.
In bottom of double boiler, heat about 1 inch of water to boiling.
Combine butter, marshmallows and salt in top of double boiler, over hot water. Stir until melted together.
Stir in food coloring to desired shade.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir gently to coat.

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: Mix all together well and spread in 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon herb sauce for broccoli
directions: Melt butter flavor Crisco in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, lemon peel, dill weed and salt.
Blend in half and half.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine salmon, crumbs, chopped onion, butter and salt.
Combine milk and egg.
Add to salmon mixture and mix thoroughly.
Shape into a loaf on a greased shallow baking pan or in 7 1/2 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with piquant sauce or creamed peas.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip angel cookies
directions: Beat margarine, shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Blend.
Stir in chips.
Roll dough into small balls, roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a crock-pot.
This is done when heated through and cheese is melted good.
I usually double this recipe.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish fillets in baking dish.
Pour tomato soup, undiluted over fillets.
Sprinkle with parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: party scramble
directions: To Microwave:
Place butter in 2-cup glass measure. cover with waxed paper; microwave on High 45 seconds or until melted.
Stir in soup mix.
In 4-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour butter mixture over cracker mixture; toss to coat well.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 5 minutes or until hot, stirring twice during heating.
Cool.
Store mixture in airtight container.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in the eggs.
Add crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Add bread cubes and milk.
Mix altogether and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: old time applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased and floured pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops on each side, sprinkling with salt and pepper in oil.
Remove from skillet and drain.
Add celery, onion and pepper.
Add rice to skillet.
Cook until vegetables are tender and rice is golden.
Stir in thyme and broth.
Place chops on top of rice.
Cover and bake 30 minutes, until tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: baked tomato spaghetti
directions: Cut tomatoes in half lengthwise and set, cut sides up, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Mix garlic, 1/3 cup of parsley, and 2 tablespoons olive oil; pat mixture over cut halves of tomatoes.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons oil over tomatoes.
Bake at 425° until browned on top, 60 to 70 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate for 2 hours.
Spread wings on foil lined baking pan and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Baste every 20 minutes.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple (drained).
Add 1/4 cup milk. Stir until thick.
Add most of pecans and stir.
When pretty thick, smooth and sprinkle remaining pecans on top.
Refrigerate.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over Minute rice.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix with Cheez Whiz, oleo, soup and rice.
Put in 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot through.

title: church windows
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate bits; cool.
Add chopped pecans and marshmallows.
Mix and form 2 logs from the mixture.
Roll in coconut or powdered sugar on waxed paper.
Wrap in waxed paper or aluminum foil; put in refrigerator to cool.
Slice in thin slices.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Halve chicken breasts and wrap each half in bacon.
Cover the bottom of a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish with chipped beef. Arrange chicken on top of this.
Blend soup and sour cream; pour over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate at this point, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.
(Double mushroom soup and sour cream for gravy over rice.)

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Break 1/2 cake into 50 cent size chunks and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover with 1 Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 3 Butterfinger candy bars (crushed) on top.
Repeat.
Top with maraschino cherries.

title: summer dip
directions: Combine pudding and milk at low speed until well blended. Fold in Cool Whip and Amaretto.
Chill.
Serve with cut up cantaloupe or other fruits.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together butter, nuts and flour.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 cup Cool Whip container and add to first layer in pan.
Mix pudding and milk and add as next layer in pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top before serving.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Place sugar, salt, eggs, evaporated milk and vanilla into a bowl; mix well.
Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler.
Add to other mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° until set (about 30 to 40 minutes).

title: artichoke pie
directions: Cook rice as directed; cool.
Drain artichokes, reserving liquid and chop.
Combine rice, artichokes, liquid, onion, pepper and olives.
Mix gently.
Add seasonings and mayonnaise.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Season chicken pieces.
Keep out small amount of mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place chicken pieces over rice mixture.
Put small amount of reserved mushroom soup on top of each piece of chicken; sprinkle with a little of the dry onion soup mix.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last 15 minutes to brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large pan.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and next 4 ingredients.
Gradually add potato flakes; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with thyme sprigs, if desired, and serve immediately.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: tuna toss
directions: Combine macaroni with tuna, celery, tomato, onion, cucumber, olives, green pepper and eggs. Blend together mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper. Toss dressing with macaroni mixture.

title: dream cake pudding
directions: Line deep dish bottom and sides with slices of pound cake. Combine Eagle Brand milk, instant vanilla pudding mix and cold water.
Chill at least 5 minutes.
Whip cream and fold in strawberries and bananas, then fold into pudding, milk and water chilled mixture.
Pour into dish lined with pound cake.
Garnish with fresh strawberries and chill until very cold and set.

title: lemonade
directions: In large pitcher,
dissolve sugar in ReaLemon, add water. Serve over ice.
Garnish as desired.

title: oil pastry
directions: Stir together flour and salt.
Pour oil and cold water into measuring cup (do not stir).
Add all at once to flour mixture. Stir with fork.
Form into 2 balls; flatten dough slightly.
Roll each between 2 (12-inch) squares of waxed paper.
Peel off top sheet of waxed paper and fit dough, paper side up, into pie plate. Remove paper.
Fill with favorite filling and repeat with top crust.
Makes 2 (8 or 9-inch) crusts.

title: down home navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans well, cover with cold water and soak for 2 hours. Place meat in pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Add celery, onion, bay leaf and navy beans.
Cover pot and cook slowly until beans are almost done.
Add salt, pepper and tomatoes. Bring to a boil and then simmer until beans are very tender.
If necessary, add more water and a small can of tomatoes (diced).

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread butter on one side of each slice of bread.
Spread other side with Thousand Island dressing.
On 4 slices, arrange corned beef, cheese and sauerkraut evenly over Thousand Island dressing.
Top with remaining bread, placing buttered side out.

title: sausage and hamburger dip
directions: Crumble sausage and brown. Add ground meat and onion, then brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Add Velveeta cheese, mushroom soup and picante sauce.
Cook slowly until all ingredients mix smoothly. This serves well in a crock-pot on lowest setting.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt together well. Roll into small balls. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish heirloom cookies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend well at low speed. Shape into balls or crescents, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Do not brown.
Roll warm cookies in additional confectioners sugar.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Stir and add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture; beat well.
Spread on large cookie sheet (15 x 10-inch).
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: slim 'n trim macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine macaroni, sharp cheese, onion and parsley. In blender combine cottage cheese, milk and mustard.
Process until smooth.
Pour over macaroni mixture and stir.
Add salt and pepper.
Turn into 2-quart casserole coated with nonstick spray.
Crumble bacon and mix with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook the spaghetti according to package directions.

title: allison's lemon-zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 loaf pans, 5 x 9-inch, with nonstick spray.
Rinse and grate zucchini.
Do not peel.
Place flour, baking powder and walnuts in medium bowl.
Blend and set aside.
Place oil, sugar, lemon peel and lemon juice in large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition until well mixed.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture.
Blend.
Add shredded zucchini and mix well.
Pour batter into 2 loaf pans.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir in enough milk to dissolve.
Beat in egg yolks; add rest of milk.
Cook until thick; add butter and vanilla.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine water, egg and funnel cake mix. Stir until smooth. This is enough batter to make 9 (5 inch) funnel cakes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix butter, flour and water to make a white sauce.
Pour over leftover Irish potatoes.
Add large amount of grated cheese.
Heat in oven until potatoes are warm and cheese is melted.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Chill bowl.
Let sherbet sit at room temperature before serving.
Put sherbet in bowl.
Pour ginger ale or champagne at side of bowl.
Makes 1 punch bowl.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 12-inch glass cake pan.
Take apart crescent roll strips and spread apart in bottom of pan.
Brown 1 pound sausage and drain real good.
Sprinkle on top of dough.
Cover with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over rest and bake at 375° for 15 minutes until set good.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in greased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples. Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass gallon jar.
Cap it.
Put it away for 30 days.
Enjoy!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cream together with butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until set, about 50 minutes.
Makes 2 deep dish pies.
May be frozen.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crush chocolate wafers into very fine crumbs and add melted butter.
Press evenly into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add mashed bananas. Sift baking soda, salt and flour together, then add to mixture and mix well.
Add nuts.
Mix again.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 375° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Do toothpick test.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine stuffing mix, cheese, parsley and garlic.
Set aside. Dip pieces of chicken in melted butter, then in stuffing, coating thoroughly.
Place chicken pieces, not touching, on cookie sheet or shallow pan, skin side up.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterscotch banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine bananas, sugar, eggs and butter; beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture alternately with milk; mix well until blended.
Stir in the chopped pecans and butterscotch morsels.
Pour batter equally into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: after school shake
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups ice in blender. Peel and cut bananas. Add to blender. Add all remaining ingredients except ice. Blend on high until smooth. Add remaining ice. Blend on high until smooth. Makes 4 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugars and eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Gradually add to make soft dough (may chill overnight).
Form dough into 1-inch balls.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and salt in bowl.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Mix sugar and vinegar together until sugar is dissolved. Squeeze liquid from cucumbers.
Place in freezer bags; freeze up to 3 months.

title: quick frosty drink
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender using the on/off switch high speed until smooth with a milk-shake consistency.
Serve promptly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, egg, cheese and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and spoon into lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with stuffing mix; dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: woodford pudding
directions: Mix all together well.
Bake in pudding dish at 375° for 45 minutes or until lightly firm.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onions, peppers, celery and pimientos in oleo.
Put layers of the peas, then the sauteed vegetables and chestnuts. Pour the mushroom soup over this.
Use buttered bread crumbs and toasted almonds on top.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: egg pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and add margarine.
Add sugar, lemon and milk.
Mix well. Pour into two 9-inch pie shells and bake until brown.

title: hot crab souffle
directions: Cube four slices of bread and place in a three-quart baking dish.
Mix crab, mayonnaise, onion, pepper and celery.
Spoon over bread. Cube the remaining bread and place over mixture.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese and margarine.
Add flour and mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball with a fork and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and sugar.
Add 1/2 of the milk and then add well beaten egg yolks.
Add remaining milk and the butter.
Next, add the vanilla and cook until thick.
Put in baked pie shell. Beat egg whites to make meringue.
May use Cool Whip instead of meringue.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until forms a hard ball.
Beat egg whites and pour together.
Beat until it begins to get stiff. Then put on wax paper in little balls.

title: cheese straws
directions: Toss pie mix and cheeses together in bowl.
Add 4 tablespoons water a little at a time mixing with fork until mixture forms ball. Divide dough in half.
Roll half to 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board to approximately 8 x 12-inch.
Brush with egg mixed with 1 tablespoon water.
Sprinkle lightly with seasonings.
Cut into strips 1/2 x 3-inch long.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Do the same to second half.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer to cake rack to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 120 sticks.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Combine mayonnaise and flour in saucepan; mix well.
Gradually add milk and cook and stir constantly over low heat until thickened.
Add salt and cheese and continue cooking until cheese melts.
Cool slightly and stir in broccoli and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form and fold into broccoli mixture.
Pour mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
With tip of spoon, make slight indention around top of souffle to form a top hat.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Dilute with 2 quarts of water.
Serve hot.
Makes 16 servings.

title: appetizer cheese balls
directions: Mix together cheese and flour.
Mix in margarine.
(Work dough with hands; it may seem dry.)
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until set, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water, and salt until it forms a hard ball in the water.
Place marshmallow cream in the mixing bowl and stir in hot syrup.
Continue stirring until slightly stiff (holds a peak). Fold in nuts and flavoring.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: candied fruit cake(refrigerate)
directions: Heat milk; do not boil.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Add crushed crackers and remaining ingredients.
Press into pan and refrigerate.
Best made at least 2 weeks
ahead.

title: crispy marshmallow treats
directions: In large glass bowl, combine marshmallows and butter.
Heat at High 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir twice.
Stir until smooth.
Add cereal and stir to coat well.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup potato chips. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Serves 6.

title: fruit bread(no sugar)
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes or until mushy. Add remaining ingredients and mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or use 2 bread pans. Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
You can freeze this.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine hamburger, 1 teaspoon mustard, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 cup ketchup, oats, egg, salt, pepper and seasoning salt.
Place half of mixture in loaf pan.
Layer with Cheddar cheese.
Then mix together 1 teaspoon mustard, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 cup ketchup, brown sugar and water and place 1/2 of sauce on top of cheese.
Layer with remaining meat mixture and top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oven ratatouille(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine vegetables in a deep 3 to 4-quart baking dish with onion, basil and oil.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for about 1/2 hour. Then, reduce to 350° for 1 hour.
Baste with juices occasionally. Season to taste.
(I eliminate salt and pepper.)
Serve at any temperature.
Good on toast.
Can use as a dip.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Slowly stir in hot milk; cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Stir a little hot mixture into well beaten egg yolks and pour back in boiler.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and cool until warm.
Peel bananas; slice in crust.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Combine vegetables and garlic with tomato sauce.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese, spices and grated Mozzarella cheese.
Wet lasagna noodles with hot water and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer veggie sauce and cottage cheese mixture over noodles until the mixtures are gone.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook 45 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes longer.
(Check the noodles before serving.

title: popovers
directions: Grease muffin pan or spray with no stick spray.
Beat eggs well and blend in milk.
Add flour and salt; beat mixture until smooth.
Pour 1/3 cup of mixture into each muffin cup.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana split pie
directions: Bake and cool pastry.
Thinly sliced bananas.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and arrange on bottom of pastry shell.
Spread ice cream over bananas.
Freeze until firm.
Spread dessert topping over ice cream.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle
with nuts.
Freeze again until firm.
Serve with canned chocolate sauce.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine ingredients; cook in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center springs back.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; add seasonings.
Cook macaroni and drain.
To the meat, add corn and mix.
Put into a greased casserole dish and add 1 tablespoon of butter in bits on top. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: christmas custard
directions: Mix pudding with pint of
milk and beat with mixer 5 minutes. Add cream (unwhipped) and beat 3 minutes. Add other ingredients and mix well while scraping side of the bowl. Refrigerate.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Put lid on jar tightly and add gift tag with ribbon.

title: vanilla wreaths(danish)
directions: Mix all three ingredients lightly together into a dough and set aside to cool for about 30 minutes or overnight.
Grease cookie sheet.
Using a pastry tube, squirt dough out onto the table in long strips.
Cut into lengths of about 3 inches and form into rings.
Bake in 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until pale golden. Makes approximately 150.

title: jennifer's wassail
directions: Simmer all but vodka, lemons and oranges for 30 minutes. Garnish with slices of orange and lemon.
Pour in vodka.
Serve warm.
Makes 32 punch cups.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add cream cheese and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each is added.
Mix in flour and then vanilla.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: ultra low-fat lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles per directions on box.
Brown turkey meat in skillet; after it's cooked, pour meat into colander and run hot water over it.
This will rinse off extra fat from the meat. Return turkey to skillet.
Add pasta sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
In a 2-quart casserole layer half of noodles, cottage cheese, shredded Mozzarella and meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Let set 10-15 minutes before serving. Best if mixed night before.

title: a+ pound cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat until very smooth. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour or until center tests done at 350°. Start in cold oven.

title: skillet green beans
directions: Heat skillet to medium-high and add enough butter to coat well. Add green beans and a little water to skillet. Let water cook away. Add sliced almonds and seasoned salt; stir-fry lightly. Remove from skillet and serve.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In a
large
pan,
melt
butter.
Add
enough
flour to absorb melted
butter,
stirring	constantly.
When butter is totally absorbed,
add
milk (approximately 1 quart) to make a sauce.
Add soup and cheese; mix well until cheese is melted. Add tuna,
salt and pepper; mix.
If mixture seems too thick, add a
little
more milk.
Cook
noodles according to package directions.
Add
to sauce;
mix
well.	Pour into a buttered casserole;
sprinkle with
bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until crumbs are brown.

title: chicken noodle divan
directions: Thaw broccoli just enough to separate.
Cook noodles 3 minutes in boiling salted water; drain.
Combine soup and milk; add noodles.
Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with broccoli and cheese.
Coat chicken as directed.
Arrange on noodles.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef burgundy stew
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Pour off fat.
Add broth, wine, tomatoes, bay leaf, garlic and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for approximately 2 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes and mushrooms.
Cook 30 minutes more until the vegetables are tender. Remove bay leaf.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix condensed milk and marshmallows and let set overnight. In the morning, add cherries, nuts, raisins, pineapple and milk. Mix all together well.
Put crumbled graham crackers into tube pan.
Pack all the above mixture into the tube pan on top of the crackers.
Put in refrigerator for at least 12 hours.
Slide knife around the edge and turn out on plate.
Keeps well!

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and milk (add milk gradually so it won't make lumps).
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Add mixture to margarine and stir.
Pour in peaches.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Place flour in brown paper bag; add chicken.
Twist top of bag to seal and shake until chicken is well coated.
Heat lard and butter in a large frypan with cover.
Add chicken, skin side down and brown quickly on all sides.
Return to low heat; cover and cook 35 to 45 minutes, turning chicken once.
Remove from pan; drain on paper towels.

title: big wheel sandwich
directions: Slice bread horizontally into 6 equal layers using electric or serrated knife.
Spread horseradish or honey mustard on first layer, and top with roast beef and second bread layer.
Spread mayo on second layer and top with Swiss cheese and add third layer of bread.
Spread mustard on third layer and top with ham and fourth layer of bread.
Cover fourth layer of bread with tomato slices, bacon and layer 5 of bread.
Top layer 5 with American cheese, onion and remaining bread layer.
Combine remaining 3 ingredients. Spread over top and sides of loaf.
Place loaf on cookie sheet. Bake uncovered at 400° for 15 minutes.
Slice into wedges.
Yields 8 servings.
Suggestion:
prepare and refrigerate.

title: the haggard cake
directions: While cake is baking, mix sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add coconut, pecans, salt and vanilla. Pour over cake while both are warm.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Run through blender the peppers and vinegar.
Drain in colander.
Add juice in saucepan with sugar.
Boil to rolling boil.
Add Certo.
Let stand for 5 minutes and put into jars.

title: julie's chinese chicken
directions: In a glass bowl, combine the chicken with the egg white and vinegar; set aside to marinate.
In a large soup pot, bring 2 quarts water to a boil.
Add the noodles and cook until they still have a bit of a bite (al dente).
Remove 1/4 cup of the pasta water and reserve.
Drain the noodles and rinse with cold water. Toss with sesame oil.

title: pan-fried venison
directions: Processing wild and domestic meat is a tradition found throughout New York State.
One way of sharing family traditions and values is when working together.
When processing venison all family members can participate.
From cutting to wrapping, labeling to freezing there is something for everyone to do.
When a "lull" occurs, heat skillet, add butter when it will sizzle.
Cook the thin slices of venison quickly and not well done, medium is best. Salt and pepper lightly.
Eat with fresh bread and good conversation.
Cooking time is less than 5 minutes.
Serves four people.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soak gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat soup to boil, stir in and dissolve cream cheese.
Add gelatine; stir and let cool. Put in bowl.
Add celery, onion, mayonnaise and seasonings.
When thick (won't get real thick), just stir well.
Add shrimp and pour in mold.
Put in refrigerator to set, usually overnight.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Beat melted chocolate.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Cover and chill until serving.
Good topped with raspberry or cherry pie filling.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: banana-nut roll
directions: Cream butter
and sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs,
at
a
time,
beating
well. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning
and
ending
with flour mixture. Stir in banana, pecans and
vanilla.
Spoon
batter
into
3 (1 pound) greased and floured coffee
cans.
Bake
at
350° for 55 minutes or until a wooden
pick
inserted
in
center comes out clean. Cool in cans 10
minutes;
remove to wire rack and cool completely.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: venison boudin
directions: Cook rice
according
to
package
directions, omitting salt (set aside).
In
a
large Dutch oven, combine the ground venison and pork fat.
Brown and drain all fat.
Add remaining ingredients,
except casings;
mix
well.
Bring
to
a
boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Add rice;
stir well and set aside.

title: terrence and mollie's chicken fingers
directions: Lightly coat chicken with mayonnaise.
Dip into bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with favorite dunking sauce.

title: sauteed okra with corn salsa
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and pepper together in a small bowl.
Add okra, tossing to coat with cornmeal mixture. Heat oil in frying pan and saute okra until lightly browned on all sides. Heat corn and picante sauce together; serve over okra.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with a fork.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Add bananas and sifted flour with soda and salt.
If desired, nuts may be added.
Pour into buttered or greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil, then add clams with broth, wine, parsley, basil, oregano and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Toss with cooked linguine.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done; peel off skin. Debone chicken and cut chicken into medium-size chunks.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt into a saucepan.
Slowly add milk and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir for two minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 tablespoons of your cooked mixture to the egg yolks and mix.
Then add your egg yolk mixture to your cooked mixture and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Pour into prepared crust and chill until firm.

title: brian's kahlua liqueur
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vodka.
Boil on low heat for 1 hour.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add vodka.
Blend together and pour into brown bottles for storage.
Makes approximately 2 gallons.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Add applesauce. Sift together flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, soda, and salt and add to creamed mixture. Add raisins and nuts. Bake one hour in a 350 degree oven.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Will serve 12 to 15.

title: pickled dilled beans
directions: Wash beans and drain.
Trim ends.
Cut beans to fit jars. Cover beans with boiling water.
Cook 3 minutes.
Drain.
Pack lengthwise into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.

title: kraut
directions: Chop cabbage; pack in quart jars.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar, then heat water to boiling and fill jars to 1-inch of top.
Seal and place jars in dark place to make.
Takes about 3 days, then you can place in cellar, dark place as in box or paper bags.

title: vietnamese egg rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil and egg roll wrappers; mix well.
Carefully separate egg roll wrappers.
Place 1 heaping tablespoonful of filling about 3 inches from one corner of each egg roll wrapper.
Fold corner over filling; roll firmly halfway up the wrapper.
Fold two side corners over filling; roll all the way up.
Seal edges with beaten egg or water.
Heat oil to 350°. Add egg rolls, 3 or 4 at a time.
